.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:24:{"acceptance":"1. EITHER: closed as 'covered by tool-calling gating' with a written justification (e.g., test or comment in the tool-calling bead's deliverables that asserts SupportsTools =\u003e SupportsStructuredOutput for all currently routed providers).\n2. OR: SupportsStructuredOutput tri-state added to ModelEntry/Surface + capabilities table, with rejection logic in evaluateCandidate, RouteRequest.RequiresStructuredOutput field, and unit tests parallel to the tool-calling bead's tests.\n3. go test ./cli/... is green (only applies to outcome 2).","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"5328120be55ab6af07a5cd35c7dc7f7a22f30f96","created_at":"2026-04-18T06:50:54.195936927Z","description":"## Lowest-priority sibling of ddx-4817edfd.\n\nSome provider/model combos don't implement JSON-mode / response_format=json_object / tool-use-required. If a bead prompt depends on structured output, today routing's blindness means the failure surfaces at dispatch.\n\nPer the parent bead's analysis, this is probably covered incidentally by the tool-calling gating sub-bead — most reasoning-tool-capable models also support structured output. This bead exists to either (a) explicitly add a SupportsStructuredOutput capability, or (b) close as 'covered by tool-calling gating' once that bead lands and we verify the assumption.\n\n## Decision gate (do this first)\n\nBefore writing code, verify the 'covered by tool-calling' hypothesis:\n- Survey the providers we currently route to (anthropic, openai, openrouter, omlx, lmstudio, ollama) and check whether each one's tool-calling support implies JSON-mode support.\n- If yes everywhere we care about: close this bead with a note in the tool-calling bead's tests / docs that asserts the implication.\n- If no (any counter-example): proceed with scope below.\n\n## Scope (only if decision gate fails)\n\n- Add SupportsStructuredOutput tri-state to ModelEntry / Surface and to capabilities.go's curated table.\n- RouteRequest.RequiresStructuredOutput bool; execute-bead sets it when the prompt requires JSON mode.\n- evaluateCandidate rejects RequiresStructuredOutput=true on SupportsStructuredOutput=no. Unknown passes with -v warning.\n\n## Files (only if decision gate fails)\n\n- cli/internal/agent/types.go\n- cli/internal/agent/routing.go\n- cli/internal/agent/catalog.go\n- cli/internal/agent/capabilities.go","id":".execute-bead-wt-ddx-4817edfd-20260418T064927-78e29296-22cadb21","issue_type":"task","labels":["ddx","phase:build","kind:implementation","area:agent","area:routing"],"notes":"Superseded by agent-1a486c2e — single routing engine in agent/internal/routing","parent":"ddx-4817edfd","priority":4,"status":"closed","title":"routing: structured-output (JSON-mode) gating — likely incidental to tool-calling","updated_at":"2026-04-18T22:43:47.191941677Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:25:{"acceptance":"1. ModelEntry / Surface in catalog.go gain SupportsTools (tri-state: yes / no / unknown).\n2. capabilities.go (new file) ships a curated default table for known harness+flavor pairs.\n3. Discovery code populates SupportsTools from /v1/models/status when the field is present in the response.\n4. RouteRequest.RequiresTools added; execute-bead sets it true for bead execution.\n5. evaluateCandidate rejects RequiresTools=true candidates known to be SupportsTools=no, with a debug reason.\n6. Unknown SupportsTools does not reject; logs at -v.\n7. Unit tests cover: known-no rejection, known-yes pass, unknown pass with warning, RequiresTools=false disables the check.\n8. go test ./cli/... is green.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"5328120be55ab6af07a5cd35c7dc7f7a22f30f96","created_at":"2026-04-18T06:50:30.504525579Z","description":"## Reject routes that can't actually run tool-calling work (sibling of ddx-4817edfd).\n\nSome omlx flavors and older local OpenAI-compat servers do not implement /v1/chat/completions with tools. Today routing fuzzy-matches them and dispatch fails with 'tools not supported' — or worse, silently returns a no-tool response that the execute-bead loop cannot consume.\n\n## Scope\n\n- Per-provider / per-flavor capability metadata: SupportsTools bool. Two layers:\n  1. Hand-curated table for known harnesses (claude, codex, opus, etc.) and provider flavors (openai, anthropic, openrouter, omlx, lmstudio, ollama).\n  2. Discovery-driven enrichment when /v1/models/status (or equivalent) advertises tool support per model.\n- RouteRequest gains RequiresTools bool (default false to preserve current behavior; execute-bead sets true).\n- evaluateCandidate rejects candidates where RequiresTools=true and the resolved (provider, flavor, model) combo is known NOT to support tools. Unknown = pass with -v warning, same pattern as context-window bead.\n- Capability metadata location: cli/internal/agent/catalog.go on ModelEntry/Surface, plus a curated table in cli/internal/agent/capabilities.go (or co-located).\n\n## Out of scope\n\n- Context-window, structured-output, effort, permissions gating (sibling beads).\n- Probing servers actively at routing time (uses cached discovery + table).\n\n## Files\n\n- cli/internal/agent/types.go (RouteRequest.RequiresTools, capability fields on CandidatePlan)\n- cli/internal/agent/routing.go (rejection in rejectIfNotViable / evaluateCandidate)\n- cli/internal/agent/catalog.go (SupportsTools on ModelEntry / Surface)\n- cli/internal/agent/capabilities.go (NEW — curated table)","id":".execute-bead-wt-ddx-4817edfd-20260418T064927-78e29296-854cb8a7","issue_type":"task","labels":["ddx","phase:build","kind:implementation","area:agent","area:routing","area:catalog"],"notes":"Superseded by agent-1a486c2e — single routing engine in agent/internal/routing","parent":"ddx-4817edfd","priority":2,"status":"closed","title":"routing: tool-calling support gating with per-flavor capability metadata","updated_at":"2026-04-18T22:43:47.285105492Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:26:{"acceptance":"1. Capability table tracks SupportsEffort and SupportsPermission per (provider, model_pattern).\n2. evaluateCandidate rejects candidates that don't honor a RouteRequest's --effort or --permissions, with a debug reason that names which capability and which provider/model.\n3. Unknown capability does NOT reject; logs at -v.\n4. Unit tests cover: known-no-effort rejection, known-yes pass, unknown pass with warning, no-effort-requested disables the check (parallel structure for permissions).\n5. go test ./cli/... is green.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"5328120be55ab6af07a5cd35c7dc7f7a22f30f96","created_at":"2026-04-18T06:50:41.86041297Z","description":"## Provider-specific honoring of --effort and --permissions (sibling of ddx-4817edfd).\n\nToday, Harness.EffortFlag is checked at routing.go:rejectIfNotViable, so harnesses without effort support are rejected when --effort is set. But provider-level gating is missing: e.g., openrouter doesn't honor --effort on non-reasoning models, and --permissions unrestricted may not apply to every harness+provider combination. Routing should reject or downgrade rather than dispatch and silently no-op the flag.\n\n## Scope\n\n- Add effort/permissions capability fields to the curated capability table (same file added by the tool-calling sub-bead, or co-locate here if that one ships first).\n  - SupportsEffort tri-state per (provider, model).\n  - SupportsPermission(permission_class) — at minimum 'unrestricted'.\n- evaluateCandidate / rejectIfNotViable: when RouteRequest names an --effort or --permissions value not honored by the resolved (provider, model) combo, reject with a clear reason. Unknown = pass with -v warning.\n- Document expected behavior for each known provider in capabilities.go comments (openrouter non-reasoning models = no effort, etc.).\n\n## Out of scope\n\n- Context-window, tool-calling, structured-output gating (sibling beads).\n- Building a 'downgrade' path (e.g., silently strip --effort and continue). Rejection is sufficient for v1; downgrade is a follow-up.\n\n## Files\n\n- cli/internal/agent/routing.go\n- cli/internal/agent/capabilities.go (shared with tool-calling bead — or new file if order differs)\n- cli/internal/agent/types.go","id":".execute-bead-wt-ddx-4817edfd-20260418T064927-78e29296-bb230ad5","issue_type":"task","labels":["ddx","phase:build","kind:implementation","area:agent","area:routing"],"notes":"Superseded by agent-1a486c2e — single routing engine in agent/internal/routing","parent":"ddx-4817edfd","priority":3,"status":"closed","title":"routing: effort/permissions gating per provider+model (not just per harness)","updated_at":"2026-04-18T22:43:47.3806568Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:27:{"acceptance":"1. RouteRequest has EstimatedPromptTokens uint32 field, zero value means 'unspecified'.\n2. evaluateCandidate rejects candidates whose known context window \u003c EstimatedPromptTokens; emits a routing-debug reason that names the model and its window.\n3. Unknown context window does NOT cause rejection; logs a warning at -v.\n4. execute-bead populates EstimatedPromptTokens with at least a char/4 estimate of the assembled prompt.\n5. Unit test in routing_test.go covers: (a) below-window rejection, (b) above-window pass, (c) unknown-window pass with warning, (d) EstimatedPromptTokens=0 disables the check.\n6. go test ./cli/... is green.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"5328120be55ab6af07a5cd35c7dc7f7a22f30f96","created_at":"2026-04-18T06:50:16.477597182Z","description":"## Smallest useful slice of capability gating (sibling of ddx-4817edfd).\n\nRouting currently does not check whether the resolved model's context window can hold the bead prompt. A 32k-context fuzzy match against an 80k-token bead prompt routes 'successfully' and fails mid-dispatch with a provider 400 or truncated output.\n\n## Scope\n\n- Add optional EstimatedPromptTokens (uint32) to RouteRequest (cli/internal/agent/types.go).\n- In evaluateCandidate (cli/internal/agent/routing.go), when EstimatedPromptTokens is set and \u003e 0, reject (or penalize) candidates whose concrete_model context window is below it.\n- Source of context window per candidate: v0.3.11's LookupModelLimits first, then catalog ModelEntry.ContextWindow (cli/internal/agent/catalog.go) as fallback. If neither is known, treat as 'unknown' — do NOT reject (avoid false negatives), but log at -v.\n- Caller side: pass EstimatedPromptTokens from execute-bead when the bead prompt is assembled (best-effort — can use char/4 heuristic if a tokenizer is unavailable).\n\n## Out of scope\n\n- Tool-calling, structured-output, effort, permissions gating (separate sibling beads).\n- Adding a tokenizer dependency. char/4 estimate is fine for v1.\n\n## Files\n\n- cli/internal/agent/types.go\n- cli/internal/agent/routing.go\n- cli/internal/agent/catalog.go\n- cli/cmd/agent_execute_bead.go (or wherever the bead prompt is assembled)","id":".execute-bead-wt-ddx-4817edfd-20260418T064927-78e29296-f5cec42a","issue_type":"task","labels":["ddx","phase:build","kind:implementation","area:agent","area:routing"],"notes":"Superseded by agent-1a486c2e — single routing engine in agent/internal/routing","parent":"ddx-4817edfd","priority":2,"status":"closed","title":"routing: context-window gating in evaluateCandidate","updated_at":"2026-04-18T22:43:47.481306052Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:41:{"acceptance":"1. TestAttempt_RateLimit_Retry_HonorsRetryAfter verifies the attempt layer honors Retry-After exactly when present.\\n2. TestAttempt_RateLimit_Retry_UsesExponentialBackoff verifies the attempt layer falls back to the published backoff schedule when Retry-After is absent.\\n3. TestAttempt_RateLimit_WiresEvaluateRateLimitWait proves the rate-limit detection path calls EvaluateRateLimitWait from try.Attempt rather than only defining it.\\n4. TestRunWithRateLimitRetry_RetryAfterRespected and TestRunWithRateLimitRetry_ExponentialBackoffWhenRetryAfterAbsent remain green after the move.\\n5. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... green.\\n6. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","created_at":"2026-05-05T10:43:40.337676361Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":".execute-bead-wt-ddx-c8f79963-20260505T104148-6e54f8ef-16072585","depends_on_id":".execute-bead-wt-ddx-c8f79963-20260505T104148-6e54f8ef-8083652e","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-05T10:43:56Z"}],"description":"PROBLEM\\nThe per-bead HTTP 429 retry policy still lives in execute_bead.go, so the attempt path does not own Retry-After parsing, exponential backoff selection, or the per-bead retry budget. That makes rate-limit behavior depend on loop wiring instead of the attempt boundary that actually issues the dispatch.\\n\\nROOT CAUSE\\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:800-851 builds RateLimitRetryConfig, installs the RecordRouteAttempt / bead-event hooks, and wraps dispatchAgentRun in RunWithRateLimitRetry.\\n- cli/internal/agent/try/attempt.go:99-137 still delegates only to legacy conflict recovery and never classifies or retries rate-limited attempts itself.\\n\\nPROPOSED FIX\\n- Move the Retry-After / exponential-backoff / budget-cap decision into cli/internal/agent/try/attempt.go on the rate-limit detection path.\\n- Keep the per-bead retry budget, per-wait cap, and routing-engine transparency hooks intact, but make them part of the attempt outcome contract rather than loop-local policy.\\n- Preserve the existing stable backoff schedule and budget-exhausted reason string.\\n- Reduce execute_bead.go to a generic caller of the structured attempt result.\\n\\nNON-SCOPE\\n- No_changes adjudication.\\n- Decomposition, push_failed, or push_conflict routing.\\n- Any change to the published backoff schedule or budget constants.\\n\\nINTERSECTIONS\\n- Absorbs ddx-c6e3db02 behavior.\\n","id":".execute-bead-wt-ddx-c8f79963-20260505T104148-6e54f8ef-16072585","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:2","area:agent","kind:refactor","story:10","observed-failure"],"notes":"Superseded by ddx-e36d7959. This generated worktree-prefixed bead ID cannot safely be used as a git ref during execute-bead bookkeeping.","parent":"ddx-c8f79963","priority":0,"status":"closed","title":"try.Attempt: relocate rate-limit retry policy","updated_at":"2026-05-05T16:20:02.653087487Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:42:{"acceptance":"1. TestAttempt_NoChanges_StaysCanonical_NotNeedsInvestigation verifies the attempt layer does not persist needs_investigation as a status and still emits triage:no-changes-* labels.\\n2. TestAttempt_NoChanges_WiresAdjudicateNoChangesContract proves try.Attempt calls adjudicateNoChangesContract rather than leaving it only in execute_bead_loop.go.\\n3. TestExecuteBeadWorkerNoChangesVerifiedClosesImmediately, TestExecuteBeadWorkerNoChangesVerificationFailsKeepsBeadOpen, TestExecuteBeadWorkerNoChangesNeedsInvestigationKeepsBeadOpen, and TestExecuteBeadWorkerNoChangesUnjustifiedStaysOpenWithLabel remain green after the move.\\n4. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... green.\\n5. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","created_at":"2026-05-05T10:43:27.591625526Z","description":"PROBLEM\\nThe no_changes contract is still adjudicated in execute_bead_loop.go after Attempt returns, so the loop owns triage labels, no_changes_count bookkeeping, and already_satisfied closure policy instead of try.Attempt. That makes the attempt contract leaky and keeps no_changes policy split across packages.\\n\\nROOT CAUSE\\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:975-1059 calls w.adjudicateNoChangesContract, increments the no_changes counter, applies triage labels, emits no_changes_* events, and closes the bead when the contract is satisfied.\\n- cli/internal/agent/try/attempt.go:99-137 only returns OutcomeReported / OutcomeSuccess / OutcomePark for conflict recovery; it does not own the no_changes policy.\\n\\nPROPOSED FIX\\n- Move ParseNoChangesRationale, verification_command execution, and triage label/event selection into cli/internal/agent/try/attempt.go near Attempt().\\n- Extend the try outcome contract so the loop only consumes structured disposition data plus cooldown/park reason/event instructions.\\n- Keep the persisted status canonical: needs_investigation is represented with triage labels/events, not a new status value.\\n- Reduce execute_bead_loop.go to generic structured-outcome handling for the no_changes path.\\n\\nNON-SCOPE\\n- Rate-limit retry handling.\\n- Decomposition, push_failed, or push_conflict routing.\\n- Any change to the canonical status vocabulary beyond the existing triage-label contract.\\n\\nINTERSECTIONS\\n- Absorbs ddx-b24e9630 behavior.\\n","events_attachment":".execute-bead-wt-ddx-c8f79963-20260505T104148-6e54f8ef-8083652e/events.jsonl","id":".execute-bead-wt-ddx-c8f79963-20260505T104148-6e54f8ef-8083652e","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:2","area:agent","kind:refactor","story:10","observed-failure"],"notes":"Superseded by ddx-71a48703. This generated worktree-prefixed bead ID failed execute-bead ref preservation because it is not a valid git ref path component.","parent":"ddx-c8f79963","priority":0,"status":"closed","title":"try.Attempt: relocate no_changes adjudication and labels","updated_at":"2026-05-05T16:16:59.135252516Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:43:{"acceptance":"1. TestAttempt_DeclinedNeedsDecomposition_ParksWithStructuredEvent verifies try.Attempt returns the decomposition recommendation and park instructions rather than leaving the loop to classify it.\\n2. TestAttempt_PushFailed_ParksWithCooldown and TestAttempt_PushConflict_ParksWithCooldown verify the attempt layer owns the push-failed and push-conflict parking behavior.\\n3. TestExecuteBeadWorkerDeclinedNeedsDecompositionParksBead, TestExecuteBeadWorkerPushFailedStaysOpenAndParks, TestExecuteBeadWorkerPushFailedCooldownCappedAt24h, and TestExecuteBeadWorkerPushConflictParksAndEmitsEvent remain green after the move.\\n4. TestClaimRefusesPushFailedBead still fails loudly until the operator clears execute-loop-last-status.\\n5. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... green.\\n6. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","created_at":"2026-05-05T10:43:49.446624092Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":".execute-bead-wt-ddx-c8f79963-20260505T104148-6e54f8ef-e209db79","depends_on_id":".execute-bead-wt-ddx-c8f79963-20260505T104148-6e54f8ef-8083652e","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-05T10:43:56Z"}],"description":"PROBLEM\\nThe execute loop still owns the terminal routing for declined_needs_decomposition, push_failed, and push_conflict. Those outcomes are not just presentation details: they decide whether a bead is parked, which event is emitted, and whether the claim is released, so keeping them in the loop means try.Attempt does not own the full outcome classification contract.\\n\\nROOT CAUSE\\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:1063-1160 branches inline on ExecuteBeadStatusDeclinedNeedsDecomposition, ExecuteBeadStatusPushFailed, and ExecuteBeadStatusPushConflict, emits the corresponding events, and applies the cooldowns.\\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_status.go:320-333 classifies push_failed / push_conflict from a merged outcome, but the loop still performs the actual parking and event emission.\\n- cli/internal/agent/try/attempt.go:99-137 only returns the legacy conflict-recovery outcome and does not yet absorb these routes.\\n\\nPROPOSED FIX\\n- Extend cli/internal/agent/try/attempt.go so decomposition and push-failure / push-conflict policies return structured disposition + cooldown + event instructions.\\n- Preserve the current event payloads and labels (decomposition-recommendation, push-failed, push-conflict) and keep the cooldown caps unchanged.\\n- Remove the corresponding branches from execute_bead_loop.go so the loop only consumes the structured attempt result.\\n- Keep push_failed claim refusal and cooldown persistence semantics intact.\\n\\nNON-SCOPE\\n- No_changes adjudication.\\n- Rate-limit retry policy.\\n- Any change to the push-failure / push-conflict status taxonomy.\\n\\nINTERSECTIONS\\n- Preserves ddx-fba752b9 / ddx-af54ebf3 / push-conflict behavior while moving ownership into try.Attempt.\\n","id":".execute-bead-wt-ddx-c8f79963-20260505T104148-6e54f8ef-e209db79","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:2","area:agent","kind:refactor","story:10","observed-failure"],"notes":"Superseded by ddx-fe1bed9d. This generated worktree-prefixed bead ID cannot safely be used as a git ref during execute-bead bookkeeping.","parent":"ddx-c8f79963","priority":0,"status":"closed","title":"try.Attempt: relocate decomposition and push outcome routing","updated_at":"2026-05-05T16:20:03.509880832Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:44:{"acceptance":"1. runWorker exec's ddx work as a child process; in-process worker.Run call deleted from this code path. 2. Child process PID is recorded on WorkerRecord; watchdog SIGTERM/SIGKILL via PID still functions (existing test scenarios pass with subprocess-stub). 3. Progress events from child reach the parent via /api/workers/{id}/event (or the per-worker event sink), and SSE subscribers still see them (graphql_subscription_worker_test.go assertions hold). 4. Stop() cancels ctx AND signals the child PID; no orphans; existing workers_stop*_test.go assertions hold against subprocess-stub. 5. workers_test.go, workers_costcap_test.go, workers_gates_test.go, workers_watchdog_test.go, workers_wake_test.go, workers_reap_unix.go, workers_stop*_test.go, workers_e2e_test.go updated to use subprocess-stub instead of BeadWorkerFactory injection. 6. handleStartExecuteLoopWorker untouched — still uses ExecuteLoopWorkerSpec (deletion deferred to 7b). 7. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/server/... green; lefthook pre-commit passes.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","created_at":"2026-05-03T06:54:27.558467012Z","description":"Replace in-process runWorker (cli/internal/server/workers.go) with subprocess exec of 'ddx work'. The existing /api/workers/register + /api/workers/{id}/event endpoints (ADR-022 step 1) become the parent server's window into the child process. Keep ExecuteLoopWorkerSpec struct in place for now — handler still calls StartExecuteLoop(spec); spec is translated to argv/env at the exec call site. Watchdog SIGTERM/SIGKILL works via the existing PID field on WorkerRecord. Drop in-process land-coordinator coupling, in-process post-merge reviewer, in-process cost-cap, in-process route-preflight from this code path — all of those now live inside the child 'ddx work' process. Update workers_test.go and related package tests that injected BeadWorkerFactory: replace in-process injection with subprocess-stub (a tiny shell or built-in test binary that simulates ddx work's exec contract). Lifecycle/Stop/wake/reap behaviours preserved by reading the child's worker-events.jsonl + signalling the PID.","events_attachment":".execute-bead-wt-ddx-eccc6efb-20260503T065047-61e4ed20-c4de2d6e/events.jsonl","id":".execute-bead-wt-ddx-eccc6efb-20260503T065047-61e4ed20-c4de2d6e","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:2","area:server","kind:refactor","adr:022"],"parent":"ddx-eccc6efb","priority":2,"status":"closed","title":"ADR-022 step 7a: workers.go runWorker → exec ddx work subprocess (progress via /api/workers/{id}/event, watchdog via PID)","updated_at":"2026-05-03T06:55:13.55742866Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:45:{"acceptance":"1. cli/internal/server/workers.go:runWorker exec's the resolved ddx binary (os.Executable() with DDX_EXECUTABLE override) with subcommand 'work' and a flag-vector derived from ExecuteLoopWorkerSpec. No in-process call to worker.Run remains in this code path.\n2. WorkerRecord.PID is populated with the subprocess PID before the exec returns to StartExecuteLoop; signal-based Stop and watchdog reaping continue to work against the child PID (TestStopExecuteLoopWorker_KillsSubprocess covers SIGTERM→SIGKILL grace).\n3. Progress events from the child reach the parent's drainProgress goroutine via the existing /api/workers/\u003cid\u003e/event ingestion path (server.go:884). At least one new test TestRunWorker_ProgressBridge_FromChild asserts that an event POSTed by the child appears on a subscribed SSE channel.\n4. BeadWorkerFactory is deleted from WorkerManager. workers_test.go/workers_e2e_test.go/workers_stop_propagation_test.go/workers_route_preflight_test.go/workers_config_test.go/graphql_adapters_default_profile_test.go updated: tests that depended on injecting an in-process executor are rewritten using the test-reentry pattern (ddx-work-stub) or deleted with rationale comment if the semantics moved into cli/cmd/* tests.\n5. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/server/... ./cmd/... green; lefthook run pre-commit passes.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","created_at":"2026-05-03T22:59:39.685160971Z","description":"PROBLEM: cli/internal/server/workers.go:runWorker runs the bead-execution loop in-process, knitting together LandCoordinator, DefaultBeadReviewer, CostCapTracker, RoutePreflight, ExecuteBeadWorker, ProgressCh→drainProgress, WakeCh, BeadWorkerFactory injection, and watchdog phase-stall tracking — all of which contradict ADR-022's autonomous-default model where workers are subprocesses identical to operator-launched 'ddx work'.\n\nROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE: cli/internal/server/workers.go:658-940 (runWorker) builds an in-process executor closure (singleTierAttempt at lines 679-747), wraps it with a CostCap tracker (lines 753-797), wires a DefaultBeadReviewer (lines 801-809), and calls worker.Run(ctx, rcfg, ExecuteBeadLoopRuntime{...}). All of this duplicates work that 'ddx work' (cli/cmd/work.go → cli/cmd/agent_cmd.go:runAgentExecuteLoopImpl) already does, just inside the parent server process.\n\nPROPOSED FIX: Replace the in-process worker.Run(...) call with exec.CommandContext(ctx, dddxBin, 'work', \u003cflags\u003e) where dddxBin = os.Executable() (override-able via DDX_EXECUTABLE env for tests). Project root passed via --project flag or DDX_PROJECT_ROOT env. Provider/harness/model/profile/effort/poll-interval/once/no-review/review-harness/review-model/label-filter/model-ref translated to existing ddx work flags. Capture child PID into WorkerRecord.PID (already a field at workers.go:147). Stop() and the watchdog already signal via PID (workers.go:1070, 1279) — verify the cross-process path works; SIGTERM with kill grace then SIGKILL.\n\nProgress event ingestion changes: child process emits via workerprobe to /api/workers/\u003cid\u003e/event (this endpoint exists, server.go:884). The parent's WorkerManager subscribes to those events (in-memory derived view from the workers ingestion handler) and forwards into the per-subprocess workerHandle.progressCh so existing SSE subscribers and drainProgress logic continue to work. Mapping: parent records the WorkerRecord.id at exec time; child registers with /api/workers/register and gets a probe-issued worker_id; parent correlates by ProjectRoot + ExecutorPID + StartedAt window.\n\nDrop in-process LandCoordinator/Reviewer/CostCap/RoutePreflight wiring inside runWorker (they now run inside the child). LandCoordinators registry stays for the existing inline 'ddx work' path (cli/cmd/agent_cmd.go:1714).\n\nWakeCh: replace with SIGUSR1 to the child (or document as no-op for the v1 of this refactor; WakeProject still walks workers but only sends to live in-process handles — kept null-safe for subprocess workers).\n\nBeadWorkerFactory: removed. Tests that previously injected a fake executor migrate to either (a) reentry-stub mode where the test binary acts as 'ddx work' via go test re-exec pattern, or (b) deletion as no-longer-applicable (semantics now live in cli/cmd/* tests).\n\nNON-SCOPE: handleStartExecuteLoopWorker rewrite (covered by 7b). Deletion of ExecuteLoopWorkerSpec struct (covered by 7b). End-to-end real-claude integration (covered by 7c). UI/GraphQL surface changes (already covered by ADR-022 step 5).","id":".execute-bead-wt-ddx-eccc6efb-20260503T225413-91120fa0-5be5f460","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:2","area:server","kind:refactor","adr:022"],"parent":"ddx-eccc6efb","priority":2,"status":"closed","title":"ADR-022 step 7a: workers.go runWorker exec's ddx work subprocess (parent-side plumbing)","updated_at":"2026-05-03T23:00:18.503933642Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:46:{"acceptance":"(1) Two byte-frozen fixture files land under cli/internal/agent/testdata/reviewer/, captured from real on-disk artifacts (not synthesized):\n  - bead-jsonl-oversized-line.jsonl — a 161,121-byte JSONL row from axon's .ddx/beads.jsonl (captures the real oversized-body-in-beads pattern; the originally cited 1.46MB row from nexiq was not locally recoverable, but this fixture still exceeds the default bufio.Scanner 64KB cap and is representative).\n  - reviewer-stream-oversized-body.jsonl — a 2,688,260-byte reviewer stream row from axon's .ddx/agent-logs/sessions.jsonl (captures the \"full stream written into event body\" pattern).\n(2) A README (testdata/reviewer/README.md) cites source paths, capture date, pre-fix failure mode, and expected post-fix behavior per fixture; also documents the two fixtures that were NOT locally recoverable and the consumer bead each deferred to:\n  - reviewer-stream-approve-misextracted.jsonl → defer to ddx-f7ae036f, which will capture live under the current stream shape once the parser lands.\n  - bead-closed-no-evidence.jsonl → defer to ddx-e30e60a9, which may construct a synthetic state for its invariant test citing this README.\n(3) Fixtures load cleanly (syntactic/format validity only); behavior-specific failing tests live on the consumer beads (ddx-f8a11202, ddx-738edf47), not here.\n(4) Fixtures pin to v0.6.0-era ddx-agent output. A v0.7.0 capture is filed as a one-line follow-up after ddx-e7254128 lands (e7254128 is already closed; follow-up can piggyback on any wave:2 bead's incidental capture).","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","created_at":"2026-04-20T14:04:11.722314718Z","description":"Pre-requisite for the three reviewer bugs (ddx-f7ae036f, ddx-f8a11202, ddx-738edf47) and the closure invariant (ddx-e30e60a9). Codex plan review suggested landing shared fixtures first so the three reviewer fixes are tested against real artifacts, not regex-guess-driven.\n\n## Work\n\nCapture real-world failure artifacts from the review-malfunction-report into cli/internal/agent/testdata/ (or equivalent location next to the reviewer code):\n\n1. `reviewer-stream-approve-misextracted.jsonl` — a captured stream the reviewer emitted that ended with APPROVE but the current parser records as BLOCK. Target: drive ddx-f7ae036f's regex tests.\n2. `reviewer-stream-oversized-body.jsonl` — ~2MB synthetic reviewer response. Target: drive ddx-f8a11202's truncation + artifact-reference assertions.\n3. `bead-jsonl-oversized-line.jsonl` — a beads.jsonl row with a 1.46MB event body (mirrors the real corruption the reporter hit). Target: drive ddx-f8a11202's read-side scanner-buffer regression.\n4. `bead-closed-no-evidence.jsonl` — a beads.jsonl row with status:closed and events:[]. Target: drive ddx-e30e60a9's invariant test.\n\nEach fixture should include a short README noting its source incident, the expected pre-fix failure, and the expected post-fix behavior.\n\nNot a product change; test-infrastructure groundwork only.","events_attachment":"ddx-004eccbc/events.jsonl","execute-loop-last-detail":"infrastructure failure (deferred): agent: provider error: openai: POST \"http://vidar:1234/v1/chat/completions\": 502 Bad Gateway ","execute-loop-last-status":"execution_failed","execute-loop-retry-after":"2026-04-20T21:02:28Z","id":"ddx-004eccbc","issue_type":"task","labels":["area:agent","area:exec","kind:test","phase:build","goal:throughput-per-dollar","wave:1","workstream:reviewer"],"priority":1,"status":"closed","title":"exec: shared reviewer + closure failure-case fixtures under cli/internal/agent/testdata","updated_at":"2026-04-20T15:22:26.079263258Z"}
