.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:64:{"acceptance":"- [ ] ExecuteBead signature drops AgentRunner parameter\n- [ ] DefaultBeadReviewer.Runner field replaced with service-based execution\n- [ ] All production callers (workers.go, agent_execute_bead.go) migrated\n- [ ] Tests pass; build clean","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"7c0bffbb637b4d0576ce81dd894f179c56632131","created_at":"2026-04-19T01:14:52.050141642Z","description":"Surfaced by ddx-81f71d44 (commit 5b933103). The Runner replacement migrated production callers but ExecuteBead and DefaultBeadReviewer still take an AgentRunner parameter. Until those signatures change, m.buildAgentRunner and f.agentRunner() must construct a Runner.\n\nScope:\n1. ExecuteBead in cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go — drop AgentRunner parameter; instead take a service constructor or workDir. Internal: call service.Execute directly.\n2. DefaultBeadReviewer in cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_review.go — same pattern.\n3. Update all callers (workers.go runWorker, ExecuteBead test scaffolding, agent_execute_bead.go).\n\nThis is the biggest remaining unblocker. After it lands: f.agentRunner() and m.buildAgentRunner go away, Runner needs only the test-scaffolding callers.","id":"ddx-0411ffda","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:build","area:agent","kind:migration"],"parent":"ddx-ac5c7fdb","priority":1,"status":"closed","title":"Phase 5c: migrate ExecuteBead + DefaultBeadReviewer to service.Execute (drop AgentRunner parameter)","updated_at":"2026-04-19T01:31:46.583566659Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:66:{"acceptance":"1. fuzzyMatchInPool returns the correct match for case + vendor-prefix variants: fuzzy('qwen/qwen3.6', ['Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-4bit', 'Qwen3.5-27B-4bit']) -\u003e ('Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-4bit', true).\n\n2. Negative case: fuzzy('minimax/minimax-m2.7', ['MiniMax-M2.5-MLX-4bit']) -\u003e ('', false). Version-patch divergence does not force a match.\n\n3. Exact match still takes precedence: fuzzy('Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-4bit', ['Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-4bit', 'Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-4bit-v2']) -\u003e ('Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-4bit', false).\n\n4. Shortest-suffix tiebreak is unchanged for already-matching cases.\n\n5. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/ -run Fuzzy passes, plus at least 5 new table-driven cases covering the normalization paths.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"5328120be55ab6af07a5cd35c7dc7f7a22f30f96","created_at":"2026-04-18T01:05:30.324576143Z","description":"## Problem\n\nThe fuzzy matcher at cli/internal/agent/discovery.go:62-108 has two defects that compound:\n\n### Defect 1: strict case-sensitive prefix with no canonical-prefix stripping\n\nfuzzyMatchInPool (discovery.go:76) does literal case-sensitive prefix check:\n\n    for _, m := range pool {\n        if len(m) \u003e len(input) \u0026\u0026 m[:len(input)] == input {\n            candidates = append(candidates, candidate{...})\n        }\n    }\n\nCannot bridge 'qwen/qwen3.6' (canonical ref) -\u003e 'Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-4bit' (vidar-omlx native). Case mismatch + slash-prefix mismatch at first byte.\n\n### Defect 2: matcher collapses provider identity\n\nFuzzyMatchModel (discovery.go:62-71) pools d.AllModels() — a deduplicated union across EVERY discovered provider. Callers then do a second lookup via ProvidersForModel(match) to pick a provider, but that lookup is not gated on --provider preference. A model name appearing on any provider can leak routing to that provider even under a --provider pin.\n\nThese two defects must be fixed together. Per Opus fresh-eyes review: per-provider-pool without normalization matches even less than the current union pool. Splitting them creates a merge-conflict hazard (same file, same test surface, one coherent change).\n\n## Fix\n\nUpdate the discovery.go fuzzy-match layer as one coherent change:\n\n### 1. Normalize input and pool entries\n\nAdd canonicalization helper:\n\n    func canonicalizeModelKey(s string) string {\n        // Strip exactly ONE leading 'vendor/' segment if present (preserve\n        // path structure for future multi-segment refs — do NOT strip all\n        // slashes blindly).\n        if slash := strings.Index(s, '/'); slash \u003e 0 {\n            s = s[slash+1:]\n        }\n        return strings.ToLower(s)\n    }\n\nPer codex fresh-eyes review: ONLY the leading vendor namespace is stripped. 'openai/gpt-4' -\u003e 'gpt-4'. 'anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6' -\u003e 'claude-sonnet-4-6'. 'qwen/qwen3.6' -\u003e 'qwen3.6'. A hypothetical 'a/b/c' becomes 'b/c' (not 'c').\n\n### 2. Case-insensitive prefix on canonicalized forms\n\nApply prefix matching on canonicalized(input) vs canonicalized(pool entry). Shortest-suffix tiebreak remains. Return the ORIGINAL pool entry (preserve casing) when a match is found.\n\nNegative case: 'minimax/minimax-m2.7' vs 'MiniMax-M2.5-MLX-4bit' normalizes to 'minimax-m2.7' vs 'minimax-m2.5-mlx-4bit'. Prefix check: 'minimax-m2.5-mlx-4bit' does NOT start with 'minimax-m2.7' (divergence at '.5' vs '.7'). Returns no match. CORRECT — m2.7 is not m2.5.\n\n### 3. Per-provider variant\n\nAdd DiscoveryResult.FuzzyMatchModelOnProvider(input, providerName) that pools ONLY the named provider's models. Exact-match + fuzzy-match semantics identical to the global version, running against the narrower pool.\n\n    func (d *DiscoveryResult) FuzzyMatchModelOnProvider(input, providerName string) (model, provider string, fuzzy bool)\n\nReturns (resolvedModelID, providerName, isFuzzy) tuple. Provider identity is preserved so downstream scoring doesn't need a second lookup.\n\n### 4. Callers\n\nKeep the existing AllModels() path (useful for unpinned routing). Callers with a provider pin should use the per-provider variant first and fall back to global discovery only if the pinned provider has no match (SD-015 'soft preference' semantics: try pinned first, then broader).\n\n### 5. Exact-match precedence\n\nPreserve exact-match precedence (both case-sensitive and case-insensitive). Exact \u003e fuzzy.\n\n### 6. Known tiebreak quirk (track, don't fix here)\n\nPer Opus review: 'qwen3' matches both 'qwen3.5-27b-4bit' and 'qwen3.6-35b-a3b-4bit'; shortest-suffix picks qwen3.5. A user asking for 'qwen3' probably wants the latest. This is inherited behavior from the existing tiebreak rule and is out of scope for THIS bead — add a follow-up bead and a test documenting the current (possibly-wrong) resolution so a future change is a conscious policy choice.\n\n## Files likely touched\n\n- cli/internal/agent/discovery.go — canonicalizeModelKey, updated fuzzyMatchInPool, new FuzzyMatchModelOnProvider\n- cli/internal/agent/discovery_test.go — new cases: vendor-prefix stripping, case folding, exact-match precedence, ambiguity tiebreak, negative (version divergence), per-provider pool match, pinned-provider fallback behavior\n- New follow-up bead tracking 'prefer latest version on ambiguous tiebreak' (file in the same commit so the link is durable)\n\n## Depends on\n\nNone; self-contained discovery-layer change. Unblocks ddx-2f5a2284 (catalog/profile discovery integration) and ddx-3c5ba7cc (tier-affinity) once ddx-8610020e (Provider field) is also in place.","events_attachment":"ddx-0486e601/events.jsonl","execute-loop-last-detail":"agent: provider error: POST \"http://bragi:1234/v1/chat/completions\": 502 Bad Gateway ","execute-loop-last-status":"execution_failed","execute-loop-retry-after":"2026-04-19T03:26:50Z","id":"ddx-0486e601","issue_type":"bug","labels":["ddx","phase:build","kind:bug","area:agent","area:routing","area:discovery"],"notes":"Superseded by agent-1a486c2e — single routing engine in agent/internal/routing","parent":"ddx-2d974641","priority":1,"spec-id":"SD-015","status":"closed","title":"routing: fuzzy matcher lacks case + canonical-prefix normalization — qwen/qwen3.6 can't match Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-4bit","updated_at":"2026-04-18T22:43:46.798248643Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:72:{"acceptance":"**User story:** As an operator, clicking Drain queue on a project home page starts a worker that I can immediately see in that project's Workers view, with its state and current bead updating live.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n\n1. **Root-cause fix.** The `workersByProject(projectID:)` resolver returns all workers whose target project matches the requested id. Both Option 1 (id→path resolution) and Option 2 (store project id on record) satisfy this; implementation chooses one with a one-line justification in the PR description.\n\n2. **Regression test — project-scoped query.**\n   - Seed a ServerState with two registered projects (different paths and ids).\n   - Start one worker for each project.\n   - `workersByProject(projectID: \u003cid-1\u003e)` returns exactly worker 1.\n   - `workersByProject(projectID: \u003cid-2\u003e)` returns exactly worker 2.\n   - `workers` (global) returns both.\n   - Unknown project id returns empty list, not an error.\n\n3. **Regression test — backward compat.**\n   - A worker record on disk without a `ProjectID` field (simulating a pre-migration record) is correctly matched by the path-resolution fallback. Only required if Option 2 is chosen.\n\n4. **End-to-end validation.**\n   - Playwright: navigate to project home, click Drain, confirm, wait 2s, navigate to Workers tab. Assert exactly one new row with `state: running` and matching worker id.\n   - Same test run against a second project asserts that project's Workers tab does not show project-1's worker.\n\n5. **No regression to unrelated surfaces.**\n   - Global `workers` query still returns all workers.\n   - Worker detail page still loads by worker id.\n   - Workers live-progress subscription still patches rows in place.\n\n6. **Cross-reference.**\n   - Note on `ddx-69789664` (Workers lifecycle controls): that bead's acceptance assumed Workers pane worked correctly. Point to this bead as the prerequisite for those tests to be meaningful.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"a21580e12b66f3b5de29b066c0dc5bfff3205f61","created_at":"2026-04-22T21:01:37.307108559Z","description":"## Observed\n\nUser clicks \"Drain queue\" on the project home page. Mutation returns success with a worker id. Navigating to `/nodes/.../projects/\u003cid\u003e/workers` shows no workers — an empty table.\n\nVerified on disk: the worker record exists and is running.\n\n```\n$ cat .ddx/workers/worker-20260422T205846-f23f/status.json\n{\n  \"id\": \"worker-20260422T205846-f23f\",\n  \"kind\": \"execute-loop\",\n  \"state\": \"running\",\n  \"project_root\": \"/Users/erik/Projects/ddx\",\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nSo the dispatch worked, but the per-project workers list filters it out.\n\n## Root cause\n\n`cli/internal/server/state_graphql.go:156` in `GetWorkersGraphQL`:\n\n```go\nif projectID != \"\" \u0026\u0026 rec.ProjectRoot != projectID {\n    continue\n}\n```\n\n- `projectID` is the GraphQL argument — a project **id** like `proj-96d7ea83`.\n- `rec.ProjectRoot` is the worker record field — a project **path** like `/Users/erik/Projects/ddx`.\n\nThese are different representations and never match. With any non-empty `projectID`, every worker is filtered out.\n\nThe global `workers` resolver (`resolver_agent.go:9`) passes `\"\"` and works correctly. Only the per-project path (`workersByProject` → `GetWorkersGraphQL(projectID)`) is broken. The user's flow (dispatch from project home → navigate to project workers) hits exactly this path.\n\nNote: `GetBeadSnapshots` (state_graphql.go:49-105) handles the same concept correctly by iterating `s.Projects` and filtering on `proj.ID != projectID` — comparing id to id. The worker resolver does not use that pattern.\n\n## Proposed direction\n\nTwo options; prefer (1) for minimal change, (2) for long-term clarity.\n\n### Option 1 — Resolve id → path at the filter site\n\n```go\nexpectedPath := \"\"\nif projectID != \"\" {\n    proj, ok := s.GetProjectByID(projectID)\n    if !ok {\n        return nil // unknown project id → no workers\n    }\n    expectedPath = proj.Path\n}\n...\nif expectedPath != \"\" \u0026\u0026 rec.ProjectRoot != expectedPath {\n    continue\n}\n```\n\n### Option 2 — Store project id on the worker record\n\nAdd `ProjectID string` to `WorkerRecord`. Populate at creation time in `WorkerManager.StartExecuteLoop` via `s.GetProjectByPath(effectiveRoot)`. Filter on `rec.ProjectID != projectID`. Cleaner — the worker record carries its own identity and the query doesn't depend on runtime resolution. Requires a tiny migration (for older records missing the field, fall back to path-resolve as in Option 1).\n\nRecommend Option 2. It removes the representation mismatch for good and is cheap.\n\n## Scope note\n\nThis is a one-line functional bug with outsized impact: it's the reason the Workers page looks broken whenever used as the dashboard intends. Prioritizing P1.\n\n## Out of scope\n\n- Workers pane lifecycle controls (`ddx-69789664`).\n- Cross-project workers view — the global `workers` query already handles that.","events_attachment":"ddx-05b4cc9d/events.jsonl","execute-loop-last-detail":"escalation exhausted: unsupported model \"minimax/minimax-m2.7\" for harness \"gemini\"; supported models: gemini-2.5-pro, gemini-2.5-flash, gemini-2.5-flash-lite","execute-loop-last-status":"execution_failed","execute-loop-no-changes-count":1,"feature":"FEAT-008","id":"ddx-05b4cc9d","issue_type":"bug","labels":["feat-008","feat-010","bug","graphql"],"notes":"**AC4 — Playwright e2e test missing.** The acceptance criteria require a Playwright test that navigates to project home, clicks Drain, confirms the worker appears in the Workers tab, and verifies cross-project isolation. No Playwright test was added. File to add: `cli/internal/server/frontend/tests/` (or wherever existing Playwright tests live). The test should cover: (1) Drain → Workers tab shows new row with `state: running`, (2) second project's Workers tab does not show project-1's worker.\n\nREVIEW:BLOCK\n\n`cli/internal/server/state_graphql.go` / `GetWorkersGraphQL` is not changed in the diff, so AC1’s id-to-path root-cause fix is not implemented or evidenced.\n`cli/internal/server/*test.go` has no diff adding the required two-project `workersByProject` regression coverage, global `workers` assertion, or unknown-project assertion for AC2.\nNo worker-record compatibility test is added for AC3, and the diff does not show whether Option 1 or Option 2 was chosen.\n`cli/internal/server/frontend/e2e/*` has no diff adding the required Drain queue to Workers tab Playwright flow or second-project isolation check for AC4.\nNo evidence is added for AC5 that global workers, worker detail loading, or live-progress row patching still work.\nNo note or tracker/documentation update cross-references `ddx-69789664` as depending on this bead for AC6.","priority":1,"session_id":"eb-6feb612a","status":"closed","title":"workersByProject compares project id to project path: per-project workers view always empty","updated_at":"2026-04-23T04:38:51.922352469Z"}
