mitsPreserves$' -count=1 passes. No struct ending in -GitOps or -Runner that fakes the thing under test is referenced from this test after the migration.\n\nGoverning concern: concerns.md §testing 'no mocks, period' + 'never mock the thing you are testing'. Parent: ddx-d9df348d.","events_attachment":"ddx-0629ed12/events.jsonl","execute-loop-heartbeat-at":"2026-04-24T05:06:45.272243413Z","execute-loop-last-detail":"escalation exhausted: no_changes","execute-loop-last-status":"no_changes","execute-loop-no-changes-count":1,"execute-loop-retry-after":"2026-04-21T23:34:04Z","id":"ddx-0629ed12","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:test","area:cli","area:agent","kind:refactor","workstream:fake-migration"],"owner":"ddx","parent":"ddx-d9df348d","priority":3,"session_id":"eb-aeb4c910","spec-id":"concerns.testing","status":"closed","title":"test: migrate TestExecuteBeadAgentErrorWithCommitsPreserves to real git + script harness","updated_at":"2026-04-24T05:07:44.780880514Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:79:{"acceptance":"1. ADR document at docs/helix/03-decide/ADR-XXX-worker-client-server-architecture.md exists, named appropriately, committed.\n2. ADR explicitly evaluates Proposals A, B, C (or articulates a fourth) and documents the chosen design with rationale.\n3. ADR includes the worker-server API contract: full request/response schemas for register, heartbeat, next-bead, event, result, disconnect.\n4. ADR includes sequence diagrams (text/mermaid) for: worker registration, bead claim, execute+report, server-restart recovery, graceful shutdown.\n5. ADR includes a compatibility analysis: what existing tests break, what behaviors migrate, what's a breaking change for operators.\n6. ADR specifies how --local mode collapses into the same code path (in-process API impl).\n7. ADR specifies sequencing relative to: ddx-29058e2a (spec unification), ddx-5cb6e6cd refactor children, ddx-dc157075 (stay-alive — likely subsumed).\n8. ADR includes implementation roadmap as an ordered list (with proposed bead titles, NOT actual filed beads — those come after ADR review).\n9. FEAT-006 or new FEAT amended to describe the worker contract (whichever is more appropriate per existing HELIX layout).\n10. Reviewed and approved by user before any implementation beads are filed from the roadmap.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","claimed-at":"2026-05-03T02:14:24Z","claimed-machine":"eitri","claimed-pid":"4025192","closing_commit_sha":"fabf513096b522e921020e323ef1bf4a9cf36afa","created_at":"2026-05-03T01:43:27.404796076Z","description":"Operator-observed gap: when ddx-server restarts, in-flight worker subprocesses lose their connection to the orchestrator. The current model has two execution paths (--local vs server-spawned) that diverge in lifecycle management, configuration plumbing (the dropped-flags class — see ddx-29058e2a), and observability (server can see only what it spawned).\n\nPROPOSED ARCHITECTURAL SHIFT\nWORKERS ARE LONG-LIVED PROCESSES THAT PHONE HOME TO THE SERVER VIA API. --local mode collapses to \"worker registers with itself\" using an in-process implementation of the same API. Same code path, same flags, same lifecycle.\n\nTHE ADR EVALUATES AND CHOOSES AMONG\n\nPROPOSAL A — Server orchestrates, workers are long-lived clients\n- Worker subprocess starts (either via `ddx work` CLI or via server-spawned)\n- Worker registers with server (via /api/workers/register, gets worker-id + heartbeat token)\n- Worker polls /api/workers/\u003cid\u003e/next-bead via long-poll or websocket; receives bead spec from server\n- Worker reports progress via /api/workers/\u003cid\u003e/event {kind, body}\n- Worker reports completion via /api/workers/\u003cid\u003e/result {bead-id, status, evidence}\n- If server restarts: worker's heartbeat fails → worker enters \"disconnected\" state, finishes current bead, reconnects on server return\n- If worker dies: server's heartbeat-timeout reclaims the bead\n\nPROPOSAL B — Server is optional sidecar, worker is autonomous\n- Worker runs independently; no server required\n- If a server is reachable (via .ddx/server.addr), worker emits events to it best-effort\n- Server is a passive observer, not an orchestrator\n- Restart-safe by construction (worker doesn't depend on server)\n- Loses: server-driven label filters, dynamic priority overrides, centralized cancel\n\nPROPOSAL C — Hybrid: workers are autonomous executors but yield orchestration to server when present\n- Worker checks for .ddx/server.addr at startup\n- If present: registers as managed; receives bead assignments from server's queue\n- If absent or unreachable: runs autonomously using local bead store\n- Server restart: managed workers detect via heartbeat failure; gracefully complete current bead, then either retry registration OR fall back to autonomous mode (configurable)\n\nUNIFIED API CONTRACT (all proposals)\n\nPOST /api/workers/register { project_root, harness, model_pref, label_filter, capabilities[] } → { worker_id, session_token, heartbeat_interval_ms }\nPOST /api/workers/\u003cid\u003e/heartbeat { state: idle|claiming|executing|reviewing } → { server_command: continue|pause|drain|terminate }\nGET  /api/workers/\u003cid\u003e/next-bead → { bead, attempt_id, base_rev } | { wait_for_seconds: N }\nPOST /api/workers/\u003cid\u003e/event { kind, body, bead_id } → 204\nPOST /api/workers/\u003cid\u003e/result { bead_id, attempt_id, status, evidence_dir, commit_sha } → 204\nPOST /api/workers/\u003cid\u003e/disconnect → 204 (graceful)\n\nThe existing --local mode collapses to: a worker that registers with itself (no server) using an in-process implementation of the API. Same code path, same flags, same lifecycle.\n\nOUTSTANDING BEADS THIS ADR MUST RECONCILE (overlap analysis required in the ADR output)\n\nABSORBED (implementation subsumed by the new architecture; ADR explicitly closes these as superseded once roadmap lands):\n- ddx-29058e2a (ExecuteLoopSpec unification): becomes the API request/response payload — the spec IS the wire format. Refactor concern dissolves.\n- ddx-dc157075 (worker stay-alive): ALREADY FIXED at commit 41cb762e via flat 30s poll-interval default + attempted-map reset. Whether the new architecture preserves these tactical fixes or replaces them via API-driven semantics needs an ADR decision.\n- ddx-cfedee8e (escalation: wire ladder): the ladder becomes server-side orchestration logic, not loop-body logic. ADR must specify where ladder lives in the new shape.\n\nCONFLICTS WITH IN-FLIGHT REFACTOR (refactor epic ddx-5cb6e6cd children) — ADR must resolve sequencing:\n- ddx-c8f79963 (C5: no_changes adjudication move into try.Attempt): refactors the SAME code that the API transition refactors. Either land C5 first then transition, OR fold C5 into the transition.\n- ddx-06eb05d8 (C7: uniform Guard contract + delete attempted/hookFailed maps): same surface; same choice.\n- ddx-848069a3 (C8: routing preflight to Drain startup): related to \"server-side preflight\" decision in API design.\n- ddx-9228a484 (C9: StopCondition + cost-cap, absorbs ddx-cfedee8e and ddx-dc157075): heavy overlap. ADR must decide whether StopCondition becomes a server-side concept, a worker-side concept, or both.\n- ddx-387a0178 (C13: file/identifier rename + ddx try CLI command): the ADR's new package layout (cli/internal/agent/work/) may conflict with C13's rename plan. Coordinate.\n- ddx-1d867ec1 (rename execute_bead_loop.go): same as C13.\n\nPARALLEL-SAFE (no conflict; ADR notes them but doesn't reshape):\n- ddx-5b3e57f4 (cooldown: distinguish disrupted from gave-up): the API contract makes disruption naturally observable (server sees worker disconnect → marks Disrupted). But the cooldown logic itself is independent. ADR should call out that the API design enables cleaner Disrupted classification.\n- ddx-1e516bc9 (fizeau Execute upstream gap): independent of API design.\n- ddx-4c51d33e LAYER 1, ddx-055e8d32 LAYER 2, ddx-5ae050dc LAYER 3 (GraphQL project scoping): all in cli/internal/server/graphql/. Independent of worker API.\n- ddx-9d55601f (picker bug): already fixed.\n- ddx-a946c744 + ddx-aee651ec + ddx-3e60fd84 + ddx-83440482 (REACH/checks): hook into pre_merge gate; needs to integrate with the new worker contract but doesn't block ADR.\n- All Story 6/14/15/16 frontend + backend feature beads: independent.\n\nSPEC UPDATES THIS ADR DRIVES (the ADR roadmap must include these as deliverables)\n\n- New ADR document: docs/helix/03-decide/ADR-XXX-worker-client-server-architecture.md\n- FEAT-006 (Agent Service) — major amendment: worker API contract section, --local-collapses-to-API explanation, deprecation of direct execution paths\n- FEAT-010 (Executions) — amendment: worker lifecycle now spans across server restarts; \"execution\" becomes a bead-attempt regardless of which worker performs it\n- SD-024 (Resolved Config / CLIOverrides) — possible amendment: if ResolvedConfig becomes part of the API request payload, SD-024 reshapes\n- TD-030 (Backend interface + chaos contract) — cross-reference if any\n- CONTRACT-003 (Fizeau Service) — no change required (fizeau is below the worker; the API is between worker and ddx-server, not worker and fizeau)\n\nNOT IN SCOPE FOR THIS ADR\n- Specific code changes (this TD documents the design; implementation is follow-up beads from the roadmap)\n- Multi-server federation (each server owns its workers; cross-server is a separate concern)\n- Auth beyond session tokens (the worker-server channel is local; no remote workers in v1)\n- Reshaping the bead schema (out of scope; ADR-004 owns that)\n\nOUTPUTS (TD deliverables)\n- ADR document at docs/helix/03-decide/ADR-XXX-worker-client-server-architecture.md\n- Updated FEAT-006 (or proposed amendments listed)\n- Sequence diagrams for: register, claim, execute, restart-recovery, graceful-shutdown\n- Compatibility table: which existing tests/behaviors break, which migrate cleanly\n- Implementation roadmap: ordered list of beads to file as follow-ups\n- Overlap reconciliation table: each overlapping bead (above) classified as ABSORBED / CONFLICT-RESOLVED / PARALLEL-SAFE with explicit rationale\n\nSEQUENCING DIRECTIVE (per user direction, 2026-05-03)\n- Should land BEFORE major refactor children that touch the loop body (C5, C7, C9) — otherwise they'd refactor against the OLD model and need re-doing\n- Should NOT block routine bug fixes or feature beads\n- C5/C7/C9 explicitly FROZEN until the ADR's roadmap establishes the new package layout","events_attachment":"ddx-076147ee/events.jsonl","execute-loop-heartbeat-at":"2026-05-03T02:18:24.251770287Z","id":"ddx-076147ee","issue_type":"epic","labels":["phase:2","area:server","area:agent","kind:design","td"],"owner":"erik","parent":"ddx-e34994e2","priority":1,"session_id":"eb-eca61029","status":"closed","title":"TD: client-server worker architecture — workers as long-lived API clients; server restart preserves in-flight work","updated_at":"2026-05-03T02:28:07.193355855Z"}
