.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:88:{"acceptance":"(1) `ddx agent providers` prints a table matching `ddx-agent providers` output (same providers, same statuses). (2) `ddx agent providers --json` returns valid JSON that a script can parse. (3) Implementation uses Go package imports from github.com/DocumentDrivenDX/agent/config (and related packages) — grep the new file for ReadLine / exec.Command / os/exec returns nothing. (4) `go build ./...` passes. (5) Manual: run the command against the live config (including vidar, grendel, bragi, openrouter, vidar-coder) and verify the output matches `ddx-agent providers` from the v0.3.5 binary.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","claimed-at":"2026-04-15T01:11:17Z","claimed-machine":"eitri","claimed-pid":"3766264","closing_commit_sha":"7e6fc77482d1f419a2ce951525620780085eb49a","created_at":"2026-04-14T20:34:10.463525163Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-09ea1884","depends_on_id":"ddx-3d64fd16","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-14T20:34:10Z"}],"description":"Add a new DDx CLI subcommand `ddx agent providers [--json]` that surfaces the live provider list with status. Implementation: use github.com/DocumentDrivenDX/agent/config's public APIs (agentconfig.Load, cfg.Providers, cfg.ProviderNames, cfg.DefaultName) and the provider package's live-probe helpers. Output format matches ddx-agent's `cmdProviders` exactly — NAME/TYPE/URL/MODEL/STATUS columns for text mode, structured JSON array for --json. Implementation lives in cli/cmd/agent_providers.go (new file) and registers with the existing `ddx agent` command group in cli/cmd/agent_cmd.go.\n\nIf ddx-agent's public API does NOT expose a clean \"list providers with live status\" helper (the internal probeProviderModels and related functions are not exported as of v0.3.5), file an upstream bead on github.com/DocumentDrivenDX/agent requesting a public `config.ListProviderStatus(ctx, cfg) ([]ProviderStatus, error)` (or equivalent) function before implementing the DDx wrapper. Do NOT shell out to the ddx-agent binary. Do NOT copy-paste probing logic from ddx-agent's cmd/ package into ddx.","events_attachment":"ddx-09ea1884/events.jsonl","execute-loop-heartbeat-at":"2026-04-15T01:20:47.046981462Z","id":"ddx-09ea1884","issue_type":"task","labels":["ddx","phase:build","kind:agent-routing","area:agent","area:cli"],"owner":"ddx","parent":"ddx-bd0691fe","priority":1,"session_id":"eb-b42b0ac9","status":"closed","title":"Visibility 3: ddx agent providers [--json] command","updated_at":"2026-04-15T01:21:04.717211703Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:90:{"acceptance":"**User story:** As a developer reviewing how different harness/provider/model combinations are performing, I expect the Efficacy page to load quickly on a workspace with tens of thousands of sessions, and I expect the rows to reflect every agent invocation — not just those tied to closed beads.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n\n1. **Source change.** `EfficacyRows` resolver reads from the sharded sessions index (`.ddx/agent-logs/sessions/sessions-YYYY-MM.jsonl`, per `ddx-2ceb02fa`). Bead-event read paths (`efficacyFingerprint`, `buildEfficacySnapshot`'s event loop, `attemptsFromEvidence`, `efficacyMemo`) are removed in the same PR — no dead code retained.\n\n2. **Schema parity.** Row shape and field names stay as they are today (rowKey, harness, provider, model, attempts, successes, successRate, medianInputTokens, medianOutputTokens, medianDurationMs, medianCostUsd, warning). UI does not need to change. Optional new filters (`since`, `until`, `projectId`) are added as nullable args with sensible defaults.\n\n3. **Fixture + baseline recorded.** Fixture seeds ≥10,000 session index rows across 2+ monthly shards with ≥10 distinct `(harness, provider, model)` groups. Baseline latencies (before any optimization beyond source change) written to bead notes with hardware + go-version footer.\n\n4. **First-pass perf targets.**\n   - All-time rollup on 10k-row, 2-shard fixture: p95 ≤ 150ms in-process / ≤ 400ms HTTP.\n   - Last-30-days rollup on same fixture: p95 ≤ 60ms / ≤ 200ms HTTP.\n   - Stretch fixture (50k rows × 24 shards): all-time p95 ≤ 400ms in-process / ≤ 1000ms HTTP, or **user is consulted** before choosing a new substrate.\n\n5. **DB-decision protocol (per user directive 2026-04-22).**\n   - If targets in (4) cannot be met with in-place optimization (streaming aggregation, per-shard memoization with correct invalidation, selective field read), the PR author posts a short proposal in the bead notes: measured achievable numbers, proposed substrate from {axon, sqlite, postgres}, and migration cost. Implementation of that substrate requires explicit user approval before landing.\n\n6. **Completeness test.** A fixture seeds sessions that would not appear under the old bead-event path (open-bead sessions, `ddx agent run` sessions, benchmark sessions). The new resolver returns rows for each of them. A matching integration test on the old code path (kept as a golden-output comparison for one cycle) asserts the new output is a strict superset in the cases it should be.\n\n7. **Freshness.** A session written via the sessions index writer (from `ddx-2ceb02fa`) is visible in the Efficacy query within 2s. Integration test writes a row and queries the aggregation.\n\n8. **Playwright smoke.** `/efficacy` opens, renders the rollup table, and clicks into `EfficacyAttempts` for one row — all within normal navigation budgets. Uses the 10k-row fixture; asserts the table has ≥5 rows rendered.\n\n9. **Cross-reference.** This bead is a dependent of `ddx-2ceb02fa` (sessions index must exist). If `ddx-2ceb02fa` is not yet landed when this work starts, bead notes record the stub / interim source chosen and the timeline for switching over.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"d4874cfd75778a35969c330285e33a126e359108","created_at":"2026-04-22T20:47:04.443214848Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-0a33bc5f","depends_on_id":"ddx-2ceb02fa","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-23T01:21:53Z"}],"description":"## Observed\n\nThe Efficacy page at `/nodes/.../projects/.../efficacy` loads very slowly. User feedback: efficacy should really be \"an aggregation of sessions grouped by provider / harness / model\" — which is not what the current implementation does.\n\n## Ground truth (current implementation)\n\n`cli/internal/server/graphql/resolver_feat008.go:676-833` —\n\n- `EfficacyRows` builds its rollup from **bead evidence events** (`kind:routing` and `kind:cost` on every closed bead), not from sessions.\n- Computation path: `store.ReadAll()` → for every closed bead, read its event file → filter for routing/cost → per-(harness, provider, model) aggregate.\n- There is a cache (`efficacyMemo`), keyed by a fingerprint that itself walks every event on every closed bead to compute event count + max timestamp. So cache validation costs almost as much as cache rebuild.\n- Cost shape: `O(closed_beads × events_per_bead)` on every request (cache miss) and even on cache hit the fingerprint walk happens.\n\n## Why this is wrong (per user feedback)\n\n- Efficacy is a sessions-view concept: \"how is harness/provider/model X doing?\" Sessions are the natural row. Bead events are a lossy, indirect proxy — they only exist for *closed* beads, they duplicate session state, and they force coupling between the efficacy feature and bead lifecycle.\n- The bead-event path misses: open beads with in-flight sessions, sessions that didn't close a bead, benchmark/quorum sessions, non-execute-bead invocations (e.g., `ddx agent run`).\n- The sessions feed is already being reworked into a sharded pointer index (`ddx-2ceb02fa`). Efficacy should read from that index — single source of truth.\n\n## Proposed direction\n\n### Part 1 — Reshape the data source\n\n- Rebuild `EfficacyRows` as an aggregation over `sessions.index` (the sharded index from `ddx-2ceb02fa`), not over bead events.\n- Grouping key: `(harness, provider, model)` — optionally filterable by project, bead, label, time range.\n- Metrics per row: attempts (count), successes (count + rate), median input/output tokens, median duration, median cost. Identical shape to today; only the source changes.\n- Shard awareness: time-range queries map to a shard set (same pattern as `ddx-2ceb02fa`); the default view reads current + previous shard.\n\n### Part 2 — Fixture + baseline (honor user's 1,000+ record floor)\n\n- Perf harness target: aggregate ≥**1,000 session rows** (≥ 10 distinct `(harness, provider, model)` groups) within the budget below.\n- Stretch fixture: 50,000 session rows across 24 monthly shards. Measures steady-state behavior as the index grows.\n- Baseline captured in the bead notes before any optimization.\n\n### Part 3 — Perf targets (first pass, in-place)\n\n- Default Efficacy view (all-time) on a 10k-session, 2-shard fixture: p95 ≤ 150ms in-process / ≤ 400ms HTTP.\n- Date-filtered view (last 30 days, 1 shard): p95 ≤ 60ms in-process / ≤ 200ms HTTP.\n- If in-place optimization (scope, pushdown, memoize-per-shard, streaming aggregation) **cannot hit these numbers** on the 50k stretch fixture, **do not silently change substrate** — raise the decision with the user. Candidate backends named by the user: axon, sqlite, postgres. Bring a recommendation + rationale, not a fait accompli.\n\n### Part 4 — Drop the bead-event read path\n\n- After the rewrite, remove `efficacyFingerprint`, `buildEfficacySnapshot` event iteration, `attemptsFromEvidence`, and `efficacyMemo`. They become dead weight once the source moves.\n- Evidence events on beads remain (they're bead audit trail, not efficacy data); nothing in bead lifecycle changes.\n\n## Out of scope\n\n- The `comparisons` / \"compare arms\" feature on this page (tracked separately — see companion bead).\n- Project-scope filtering UI (the backend support can be added now; the UI widget is a follow-up).\n- Cross-machine / federated efficacy rollups.","efficacy_baseline":"recorded","events_attachment":"ddx-0a33bc5f/events.jsonl","execute-loop-last-detail":"agent: provider error: provider request timeout: wall-clock 15m0s","execute-loop-last-status":"execution_failed","execute-loop-no-changes-count":1,"execute-loop-retry-after":"2026-04-23T13:19:44Z","feature":"FEAT-019","id":"ddx-0a33bc5f","issue_type":"task","labels":["feat-008","feat-010","feat-019","efficacy","perf"],"notes":"Efficacy now depends on ddx-2ceb02fa. The current worktree contains the sharded sessions index implementation at .ddx/agent-logs/sessions/sessions-YYYY-MM.jsonl, so this pass reads that substrate directly; no interim source or stub was used.\n\nSource-change baseline before per-shard memoization: fixture seeds 10,000 session index rows across 2 monthly shards with 10 distinct harness/provider/model groups, plus stretch fixture of 50,000 rows across 24 monthly shards. Measured with go test ./internal/server/graphql -run TestEfficacyRowsDateFilterAndPerfTargets -count=1 -v.\n\nSource-only results:\n- 10k all-time in-process p95: 46.87735ms (target \u003c=150ms)\n- 10k all-time HTTP p95: 47.756933ms (target \u003c=400ms)\n- 10k last-30-days in-process p95: 24.356549ms (target \u003c=60ms)\n- 10k last-30-days HTTP p95: 25.628964ms (target \u003c=200ms)\n- 50k x 24-shard all-time in-process p95: 279.266233ms (target \u003c=400ms)\n- 50k x 24-shard all-time HTTP p95: 300.428036ms (target \u003c=1000ms)\n\nFinal implementation adds shard-stat invalidated session-index memoization. Final measured results:\n- 10k all-time in-process p95: 1.368873ms\n- 10k all-time HTTP p95: 3.202329ms\n- 10k last-30-days in-process p95: 1.742706ms\n- 10k last-30-days HTTP p95: 2.049998ms\n- 50k x 24-shard all-time in-process p95: 242.886602ms\n- 50k x 24-shard all-time HTTP p95: 886.748µs\n\nDB-decision protocol: in-place session-index aggregation met the first-pass and stretch targets, so no axon/sqlite/postgres substrate proposal is required in this pass. Race-detector runs skip the perf-threshold test because race instrumentation invalidates latency targets; non-race CI enforces them.\n\nHardware/footer: Linux eitri 6.17.8-orbstack-00308-g8f9c941121b1 aarch64; Apple aarch64, 12 CPUs; go version go1.26.2 linux/arm64.\n\n`cli/internal/server/frontend/e2e/efficacy.spec.ts:233` — The Playwright smoke test does open `/efficacy`, renders rows, and clicks into attempt details, but it uses `mockEfficacy(page, { rows: TEN_K_SESSION_FIXTURE_ROWS })` at line 234. That is only 12 pre-aggregated mocked rows, not a seeded 10k session-index fixture, so it does not validate page behavior or navigation budget against the real backend fixture required by AC8.\n\nREVIEW:BLOCK\n\n**No resolver changes.** `cli/internal/server/graphql/resolver_feat008.go` is untouched. AC1 requires `EfficacyRows` to read from the sharded sessions index and remove `efficacyFingerprint`, `buildEfficacySnapshot`, `attemptsFromEvidence`, and `efficacyMemo`.\n**No fixture or benchmarks.** AC3/AC4 require a ≥10k-row fixture across 2+ shards with baseline latency measurements. Nothing seeds data or measures performance.\n**No tests of any kind.** AC6 (completeness/superset), AC7 (freshness), and AC8 (Playwright smoke) all require new test files. None are present.\n**No schema changes.** AC2 requires optional `since`, `until`, `projectId` filter args on the GraphQL query. No `.graphql` or resolver signature changes appear.\n**The result.json itself reports `task_succeeded`**, but the merge commit (`41fa9657`) it references only contains \"test(efficacy): add real-backend HTTP smoke + align UI fixture\" per git log — suggesting partial work may exist on a branch that wasn't included in this diff. The next agent should check whether commit `41fa9657` contains unreflected work, or whether the execution truly produced no implementation.\n\nREVIEW:BLOCK\n\n`cli/internal/server/graphql/resolver_feat008.go` is not changed; `EfficacyRows` is not shown reading `.ddx/agent-logs/sessions/sessions-YYYY-MM.jsonl`, and the old `efficacyFingerprint`, `buildEfficacySnapshot` event loop, `attemptsFromEvidence`, and `efficacyMemo` removals are absent.\nGraphQL schema/resolver argument changes for nullable `since`, `until`, and `projectId` are absent from the diff.\nNo fixture or benchmark changes seed 10k+ session rows across 2+ shards or record baseline/perf results in bead notes.\nNo tests are added or changed for non-bead sessions, freshness after session index writes, or old-path superset comparison.\nNo Playwright smoke test for `/efficacy` is added or changed.\nNo tracker or bead-note evidence records dependency on `ddx-2ceb02fa` or a DB-decision proposal.","priority":1,"session_id":"eb-282fb10f","status":"closed","title":"Efficacy page is slow and sources from the wrong place: rework as session aggregation, seed ≥1k fixture, raise DB decision if in-place insufficient","updated_at":"2026-04-23T23:55:48.776241989Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:92:{"acceptance":"1. Written incident report (.md or bead comment body) captures at least one observed hang with: process state, timeline, tracker state, and root-cause classification.\n\n2. Follow-up bead(s) filed for each identified root cause. Each with deterministic AC (e.g. 'add 10m wall-clock timeout on bash tool subprocess execution').\n\n3. This bead closes as 'investigation complete; see child beads for fixes'. ddx-b808df39 references this bead's findings in its implementation notes.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","claimed-at":"2026-04-18T04:31:48Z","claimed-machine":"eitri","claimed-pid":"1833233","closing_commit_sha":"1d0b3e373a618623062909694332536c74f2630a","created_at":"2026-04-18T03:01:36.338860593Z","description":"## Context\n\nddx-b808df39 (P0: ddx agent stop/kill command for hung workers) treats hung-worker remediation as an operational need, but does NOT investigate the UNDERLYING cause of the hangs. The feature is a useful escape hatch, but shipping it without understanding WHY workers hang means we'll keep needing the escape hatch.\n\nOpus fresh-eyes review (2026-04-18) flagged: 'Hung workers for 33h–142h are an operational defect independent of root cause' — the feature bead is justified, but a SIBLING root-cause investigation is missing from the portfolio.\n\n## Observed\n\nThe referenced 33h and 142h hang durations in ddx-b808df39 imply multiple incidents where an execute-bead worker process remained in-progress past any reasonable upper bound for a single bead. Needs to investigate:\n\n1. Is the worker process alive but stuck in a tool call (bash subprocess that never returns)?\n2. Is it alive but mid-LLM-call with no timeout (provider hang + no client-side deadline)?\n3. Is it dead but the bead's claimed_at never cleared (tracker-side leak)?\n4. Is the worktree locked or fsync'd in a way that prevents cleanup?\n\n## Fix direction\n\nThis bead is an INVESTIGATION, not a fix. Deliverable is a short report that:\n\n1. Reproduces or observes at least one hang incident and captures:\n   - ps / pgrep state of the worker process tree\n   - stack traces via 'go tool pprof' against the worker (if alive)\n   - Timeline from .ddx/executions/\u003cattempt\u003e/embedded/*.jsonl (last event type + timestamp)\n   - tracker claimed_at and retry_after state\n\n2. Classifies the hang into one of the four categories above (or a new category).\n\n3. Files concrete follow-up beads for each identified root cause:\n   - Tool subprocess timeout if bash hangs\n   - LLM client deadline if provider hangs\n   - Claim expiry / heartbeat if tracker-side leak\n   - File-lock / worktree cleanup if fs-side\n\n4. Recommends whether ddx-b808df39's stop/kill mechanism is sufficient as mitigation or needs additional primitives.\n\n## Relation to ddx-b808df39\n\nddx-b808df39 ships the OPERATOR TOOL to stop a hung worker. This bead finds the BUG that causes hangs. Both are needed; ship ddx-b808df39 first if the operator-tool is more urgent, then this investigation.\n\n## Non-goals\n\n- Fixing the root cause in this bead. Scope is investigation + follow-up bead filing.\n- Preventing all possible hangs (impossible). Scope is the actually-observed hang modes.","events_attachment":"ddx-0a651925/events.jsonl","execute-loop-heartbeat-at":"2026-04-18T04:50:48.095091931Z","id":"ddx-0a651925","issue_type":"task","labels":["ddx","phase:build","kind:investigation","area:agent","area:workers"],"notes":"Investigation complete (attempt 20260418T043148-1346e8a3). Report at .ddx/executions/20260418T043148-1346e8a3/incident_report.md.\n\nRoot-cause summary:\n- RC1 (PRIMARY): Runner.Run and Runner.RunAgent discard caller ctx (runner.go:239, agent_runner.go:163). WorkerManager.Stop cannot interrupt a running agent.\n- RC2: idle-reset timer instead of wall-clock deadline for non-claude paths (executor.go:154, agent_runner.go:264).\n- RC3: compaction-stuck breaker fires too late (~2h observed).\n- RC4: provider HTTP calls likely lack per-request deadlines (confirm against live hung worker).\n- BashTool subprocess hang ruled out (120s default timeout). Tracker-side / fs-lock hypotheses are downstream of RC1.\n\nFollow-up beads filed (parent=ddx-0a651925):\n- …-526efaf1 P0 [RC1] propagate caller context\n- …-b203c889 P0 [RC2] wall-clock deadline\n- …-3e3913a0 P1 [RC4] per-request HTTP deadlines\n- …-b0562380 P2 [RC3] bound compaction-stuck breaker by wall-clock\n- …-34d039b7 P1 autonomous worker watchdog (complements ddx-b808df39)\n\nddx-b808df39's operator stop/kill is a correct mitigation but NOT sufficient as sole fix — until RC1 lands, operators will keep needing it. Ship ddx-b808df39 first, then RC1 → RC2 → RC4 → RC3 → watchdog.\n\nFind child beads: ddx bead list --parent ddx-0a651925","owner":"erik","priority":1,"session_id":"eb-15287082","status":"closed","title":"investigate: root cause of 33-142h hung workers (referenced by ddx-b808df39)","updated_at":"2026-04-18T04:51:41.352578072Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:94:{"acceptance":"rg 'ExecuteBeadOptions\\\\{' cli/ returns 0 matches outside the type definition about to be retired. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./... passes.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","claimed-at":"2026-04-25T19:53:26Z","claimed-machine":"eitri","claimed-pid":"196235","closing_commit_sha":"eee160a96d8f631d1341d5bf11581db9de6fde19","created_at":"2026-04-25T14:31:28.411984342Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-0b382233","depends_on_id":"ddx-10717b12","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-25T14:31:35Z"}],"description":"Stage 3 of SD-024. Mechanical migration of any remaining sites.\n\nIn-scope:\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_e2e_test.go\n- Any cmd/ test file constructing ExecuteBeadOptions","events_attachment":"ddx-0b382233/events.jsonl","execute-loop-heartbeat-at":"2026-04-25T20:04:56.401761913Z","id":"ddx-0b382233","issue_type":"task","labels":["ddx","kind:test-migration","area:agent","sd-024","stage:3"],"notes":"REVIEW:BLOCK\n\n**Production sites not migrated** — `cli/cmd/agent_cmd.go:1738` and `cli/internal/server/workers.go:586` still construct `agent.ExecuteBeadOptions{...}`. SD-024's \"all three dispatch sites must migrate together\" principle plus this AC require these to move to `ExecuteBeadWithConfig` + `ExecuteBeadRuntime`.\n**Test sites not migrated** — `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_artifacts_test.go` (6 occurrences), `execute_bead_checkpoint_test.go` (2), `execute_bead_env_isolation_test.go` (1), `execute_bead_commit_test.go` (1) still construct `ExecuteBeadOptions{`. AC #1 explicitly covers these.\n**Verification gap** — Re-run `rg 'ExecuteBeadOptions\\{' cli/` after migration; only `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:154` (the internal `opts := ExecuteBeadOptions{` inside the legacy shim) should remain, and only if that shim is \"the type definition about to be retired.\" If the shim itself is in scope, it must also be removed.\n**Scope-vs-AC mismatch** — The bead description listed only two files; the AC is repository-wide. Either the next iter expands scope to satisfy AC #1, or the bead needs a triage decision to narrow the AC. As written, AC #1 is unmet.","owner":"ddx","parent":"ddx-0f3ae192","priority":1,"session_id":"eb-cd9ffccb","spec-id":"SD-024","status":"closed","title":"agent/test + cmd/test: migrate remaining ExecuteBeadOptions sites","updated_at":"2026-04-25T20:06:21.369875119Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:96:{"archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"7d18cb4a228d9c3d6a8d3f381e34801b2cd7da2c","created_at":"2026-04-15T01:14:36.326164034Z","description":"'ddx agent execute-loop' help says 'execute-loop scans the current project's execution-ready bead queue.' When submitting to a multi-project server, there is no way to say 'run this loop against project X'. The server picks whichever project is the current server context, ignoring the caller's CWD.\n\n## Observed\n\nFrom CWD /Users/erik/Projects/axon:\n\n  $ ddx agent execute-loop --once --harness claude --model claude-sonnet-4-6 --json\n  {\n    \"project_root\": \"/Users/erik/Projects/ddx\",  # WRONG\n    \"state\": \"running\",\n    \"worker_id\": \"worker-20260415T011331-d0a4\"\n  }\n\nI wanted the worker to pick an axon bead. The server ran the worker against the ddx repo instead. There is no --project flag, no env var, nothing in the CLI to redirect the server's project scope.\n\nCurrently the only way to target a specific project with execute-loop is --local mode (which spawns a subprocess using the caller's CWD as the project root). This defeats the purpose of having a server in a multi-project deployment.\n\n## Scope\n\n- --project \u003cpath\u003e or --project \u003cname\u003e flag on execute-loop, execute-bead, and 'ddx agent run' that tells the server which project_root to use\n- Env var fallback: DDX_PROJECT_ROOT or similar\n- Default to CWD if unset and no flag\n- Server refuses ambiguous/unmatched project names with a clean error\n- Integration test: from CWD A, submit a loop targeting project B; assert worker runs in B's project_root\n\n## Why this matters for the user's workflow\n\nWithout this, the ONLY way to drive multi-project execution from one shell is --local, which (a) loses the server's queue visibility, (b) ties the parent process to the child, and (c) negates the 'ddx agent execute-loop submits to server by default' ergonomic that execute-loop's --help promises.\n\n## Acceptance\n\n- [ ] --project flag wired through execute-loop/execute-bead/run\n- [ ] Env var fallback documented\n- [ ] Default behavior: CWD-based project detection\n- [ ] Integration test for cross-project submission\n- [ ] execute-loop --help updated to describe project targeting","events_attachment":"ddx-0b9c980a/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-0b9c980a","issue_type":"bug","labels":["helix","area:agent","area:exec","kind:bug","gap:review-loop","tier:local"],"priority":1,"status":"closed","title":"exec: execute-loop --project flag to target a specific project when server is multi-project","updated_at":"2026-04-15T06:05:45.856928108Z"}
