Stage F): the pre-dispatch\nshort-circuit outcome event is emitted as 'compare-error:\ncontext_overflow'. The same class name used in Stage C1 for review\n(see FEAT-022 §12) is mirrored on the grading side, with the event\nkind prefix adapted to the grading context. Stage F reads this name\nwhen aggregating metrics.\n\nIn-scope files:\n- cli/internal/agent/grade.go (buildGradingPrompt at :58: route arm\n  Output, PostRunOut, ToolCalls through evidence.ClampOutput; route\n  arm Diff through evidence.ClampDiff + evidence.DecomposeDiff;\n  include arm.PostRunOK as a boolean field in the prompt; implement\n  priority-ordered assembly with minimum floor: rubric + task prompt\n  + per-arm identity always present)\n- cli/internal/agent/grade.go (pre-dispatch short-circuit: if\n  assembled prompt exceeds MaxPromptBytes after all trimming, skip\n  provider dispatch and emit 'compare-error: context_overflow')\n- Tests: fixture with multi-MB arm outputs and diffs exercising\n  minimum floor preservation, PostRunOut/PostRunOK/ToolCalls\n  inclusion (bounded), pre-dispatch short-circuit event emission\n\nOut-of-scope:\n- Review path (Stage C1)\n- Section-level telemetry (Stage F)\n- Ref-only-metadata alternative for grading (rejected in round 2:\n  compare sandboxes are deleted before the record returns unless\n  KeepSandbox is set; inline-with-cap is the correct strategy)\n\nRollback: revert grade.go changes; compare tests fall back to\nprior behavior.","events_attachment":"ddx-0bbf8563/events.jsonl","execute-loop-heartbeat-at":"2026-04-25T10:36:44.5795921Z","id":"ddx-0bbf8563","issue_type":"task","labels":["ddx","kind:implementation","area:agent","area:grading","stage:C2"],"owner":"ddx","parent":"ddx-0c35470e","priority":2,"session_id":"eb-c23a7ef4","spec-id":"FEAT-022","status":"closed","title":"grading: bounded evidence assembly including PostRunOut/PostRunOK/ToolCalls","updated_at":"2026-04-25T10:37:58.122087014Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:103:{"acceptance":"ddx agent log --bead axon-abc123 shows all execution attempts for that bead in chronological order with ATTEMPT, STARTED, DURATION, HARNESS, MODEL, OUTCOME, TOKENS, COST, SESSION columns. OUTCOME is resolved from result.json when available, falls back to exit_code. Summary line printed after table. --json emits filtered SessionEntry array with outcome field. Bead with no sessions prints 'no sessions found for bead \u003cid\u003e'. Existing ddx agent log behavior (no --bead flag) is unchanged. ddx agent log \u003csession-id\u003e single-session detail view is unchanged.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","claimed-at":"2026-04-14T10:13:22Z","claimed-machine":"eitri","claimed-pid":"1412283","closing_commit_sha":"4d938dd00e470417cb39fc139c564bc3d74bd6a4","created_at":"2026-04-13T20:35:04.508596568Z","description":"ddx agent log is fully implemented (cli/cmd/agent_cmd.go lines 745-807) and reads .ddx/agent-logs/sessions.jsonl. Each SessionEntry has a Correlation map (cli/internal/agent/types.go) that includes bead_id when the session was created by execute-bead. However there is no way to filter sessions by bead — you must know the session ID in advance or scroll through all recent sessions.\n\nThis bead adds --bead \u003cid\u003e filtering and a per-bead attempt summary view to the existing command.\n\n## Required changes\n\n### 1. --bead flag on ddx agent log (cli/cmd/agent_cmd.go)\nWhen --bead \u003cbead-id\u003e is provided:\n  - Scan all SessionEntry records in sessions.jsonl\n  - Filter to entries where Correlation[\"bead_id\"] == bead-id\n  - Sort ascending by Timestamp (attempt order)\n  - Display in attempt-history table format (see below)\n\nNo change to the default behavior (no --bead = show recent N sessions as today).\n\n### 2. Attempt history table columns\nATTEMPT | STARTED | DURATION | HARNESS | MODEL | OUTCOME | TOKENS | COST | SESSION\n- ATTEMPT: 1-based index in chronological order\n- OUTCOME: merged / preserved / no-changes / error (from ExecuteBeadResult.Outcome via Correlation or result.json)\n- SESSION: truncated session ID (8 chars) for use with ddx agent log \u003csession-id\u003e\n- COST: formatted as /bin/zsh.0042 or 'local' if cost_usd == 0\n\n### 3. Outcome resolution\nSessionEntry does not directly store outcome — it stores exit_code and error. The full outcome is in .ddx/executions/{attemptID}/result.json (ExecuteBeadResult struct). When rendering the attempt table:\n  - Use Correlation[\"attempt_id\"] to find .ddx/executions/{attempt_id}/result.json\n  - Read ExecuteBeadResult.Outcome from that file\n  - Fall back to exit_code == 0 ? 'success' : 'error' if result.json is absent\n\n### 4. Summary line\nAfter the table, print a one-line summary:\n  '\u003cbead-id\u003e: N attempts, M merged, K preserved, J errors. Last attempt: \u003celapsed\u003e ago.'\n\n### 5. --json passthrough\nWhen --bead and --json are both set, emit the filtered SessionEntry array as JSON with an added outcome field resolved from result.json.\n\n## Key files\n- cli/cmd/agent_cmd.go — newAgentLogCommand() lines 745-807, add --bead flag and filter path\n- cli/internal/agent/types.go — SessionEntry struct (lines 94-122), Correlation map field\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go — ExecuteBeadResult struct (lines 30-64), artifact paths convention\n- .ddx/agent-logs/sessions.jsonl — runtime data source","events_attachment":"ddx-0c40e959/events.jsonl","execute-loop-heartbeat-at":"2026-04-14T10:25:22.090512411Z","id":"ddx-0c40e959","issue_type":"task","labels":["ux","observability","cli","agent-log"],"owner":"ddx","priority":2,"session_id":"eb-reconcile-4d938dd","status":"closed","title":"Extend ddx agent log with --bead filter and per-bead attempt history","updated_at":"2026-04-14T14:12:42.487751389Z"}
