.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:160:{"acceptance":"1. On a host where ddx agent check reports at least one LM Studio provider\n   (bragi, grendel, vidar, vidar-coder) connected, ddx agent execute-loop\n   --once --json against a ready bead routes a cheap-tier attempt to a live\n   provider without requiring --provider or --harness on the CLI.\n2. The result.json for the cheap-tier attempt records status != \"execution_failed\"\n   when the live provider accepts the request (status may be success, no_changes,\n   or a non-dispatch failure downstream, but must NOT be \"did not match any\n   provider, catalog ref, or model-route\" and must NOT be \"harness lmstudio\n   not available: not found in PATH\").\n3. New unit / integration test in the execute-bead routing package asserts:\n   given a catalog entry cheap.embedded-openai: qwen3.5-27b and a discovered\n   provider advertising qwen3.5-27b, the resolver returns that provider.\n4. New unit / integration test asserts: the lmstudio harness is treated as\n   HTTP-probeable, not PATH-probeable, so it survives harness availability\n   checks when the live-discovery path sees an LM Studio provider.\n5. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./... \u0026\u0026 go build .\n6. ddx agent doctor and ddx agent check exit 0 on a host with live LM Studio\n   providers.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","created_at":"2026-04-17T02:49:32.207204061Z","description":"Observed on 2026-04-17T02:39 during an execute-loop --once cycle against bead\nhelix-ede8085a (from /Users/erik/Projects/helix). Evidence preserved at\n/Users/erik/Projects/helix/.ddx/executions/20260417T023917-dc4a49d3/result.json\nand /Users/erik/Projects/helix/.ddx/executions/20260417T023921-e66e9375/result.json.\n\nddx agent check --verbose on this host reports live LM Studio providers:\nbragi (10 models), grendel (3), vidar (11), vidar-coder (11), openrouter (345).\nSo model discovery IS working — the gap is in execute-bead's catalog→provider\nresolution.\n\nSymptom 1 — cheap tier / embedded-openai surface\n  Routing decision: tier=cheap harness=agent model=qwen3.5-27b\n  Failure: \"model \\\"qwen3.5-27b\\\" did not match any provider, catalog ref, or\n  model-route; specify --provider or --model-ref explicitly\"\n  The user's ~/.ddx/model-catalog.yaml maps cheap.embedded-openai → qwen3.5-27b,\n  but the embedded ddx-agent harness has no provider registration that serves\n  qwen3.5-27b. Meanwhile bragi / grendel / vidar all expose lmstudio-backed\n  models and could plausibly serve it — but execute-bead never consults live\n  provider discovery when a catalog model-ref fails to resolve.\n\nSymptom 2 — lmstudio harness fallback\n  Routing decision: harness=lmstudio model=minimax/minimax-m2.7\n  Failure: \"agent: harness lmstudio not available:  not found in PATH\"\n  lmstudio is an HTTP harness (ddx agent doctor reports it as \"(http)\" and OK),\n  yet the execute-bead harness probe path-checks it like a binary CLI and\n  rejects it before any HTTP probe runs.\n\nNet effect: the auto-escalation ladder skips cheap and standard tiers entirely\non this machine and lands on smart-tier codex/gpt-5.4, defeating the\ncost-tiered routing the parent epic (ddx-4b59b816) is designed to enable.\nThe operator should not have to pass --provider vidar or --harness codex to\nroute around this — that re-introduces the hyper-specification this epic is\ntrying to eliminate.\n\nRoot-cause candidates (pick one, not both):\n  a) Extend execute-bead catalog resolution so that when a catalog surface\n     maps to a model-ref the local harness cannot serve, it consults live\n     provider discovery (the same discovery ddx agent check uses) to locate\n     a reachable provider that advertises the model, and routes there.\n  b) Teach ddx agent execute-bead that the lmstudio harness is HTTP-backed\n     and probe it via the live-discovery path instead of PATH lookup, so the\n     cheap-tier fallback from (qwen3.5-27b) → (minimax/minimax-m2.7 via\n     lmstudio) actually reaches the bragi/grendel/vidar endpoints.\n\nBoth symptoms share a root: execute-bead's harness/model resolution has no\nlive-discovery hook. A fix should close that gap.","id":"ddx-1cfce460","issue_type":"bug","labels":["phase:build","area:agent","kind:routing","goal:throughput-per-dollar"],"parent":"ddx-4b59b816","priority":1,"status":"closed","title":"execute-bead cheap tier cannot resolve catalog models to live LM Studio providers","updated_at":"2026-04-17T02:58:29.941739396Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:161:{"acceptance":"- [ ] compare.go/benchmark.go/quorum.go/condense.go and their tests live in agent (path TBD, likely internal/comparison/ or similar)\n- [ ] DDx versions deleted\n- [ ] Existing compare/benchmark functionality still callable (via agent CLI or DDx Service-thin wrapper)","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"61234fae4e9c77375230c7565d15908d816142a7","created_at":"2026-04-18T21:30:19.298454737Z","description":"Move four comparison/benchmark files upstream into agent module — they ARE the comparison-suite infrastructure the integration suite (agent-fd22bfeb) builds on.\n\nFiles (with tests):\n- compare.go + compare_test.go (comparison runner, calls into routing engine)\n- benchmark.go + benchmark_test.go (benchmark runner)\n- quorum.go (quorum strategies for comparison)\n- condense.go (output condensation)\n\nOnce landed in agent: DDx files delete; ddx agent compare command (if it exists) calls upstream via Service or via a dedicated bench API method (or stays in DDx if it is bead-orchestration not LLM-routing — depends on what compare.go actually does, decide during the move).\n\nPre-condition: routing infrastructure already moved upstream (compare.go calls RankCandidates which is now agent-internal).","id":"ddx-1d2c2e7f","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:build","kind:move","area:bench"],"parent":"ddx-ac5c7fdb","priority":2,"status":"closed","title":"Phase 5: move cli/internal/agent/{compare,benchmark,quorum,condense}.go upstream into agent (then delete from DDx)","updated_at":"2026-04-18T23:20:52.586262437Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:167:{"acceptance":"`ddx agent execute-bead` resolves governing references for both doc-ID and repo-relative path-style `spec-id` values when the target file exists in the execution snapshot; the generated prompt/manifest include the resolved path reference instead of the `No governing references` fallback; and deterministic tests cover a bead whose `spec-id` is a repo-relative path such as `workflows/README.md`.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"cee85e6565224b30b15f689fa7daac8ad5e4a12b","created_at":"2026-04-11T01:18:51.632271275Z","description":"\u003ccontext-digest\u003e\nAlpha validation run from /Users/erik/Projects/helix using `ddx agent execute-loop --once --json` against a live HELIX bead whose `spec-id` is the repo-relative path `workflows/README.md`. Evidence includes `.ddx/executions/20260411T011535-bbda19d7/prompt.md`, `.ddx/executions/20260411T011535-bbda19d7/manifest.json`, and `cli/cmd/agent_execute_bead.go`.\n\u003c/context-digest\u003e\n\n`ddx agent execute-bead` prompt synthesis failed to resolve a live path-style `spec-id` into governing references, so the generated execution prompt told the agent there were no governing references even though the referenced file exists in the execution snapshot.\n\n## Reproduction\n1. In `/Users/erik/Projects/helix`, inspect bead `helix-fef22846`; it carries `spec-id=workflows/README.md`.\n2. Run `ddx agent execute-loop --once --json` or `ddx agent execute-bead helix-fef22846 --json`.\n3. Open `.ddx/executions/20260411T011535-bbda19d7/prompt.md`.\n4. Observe the prompt includes `- spec-id: workflows/README.md` but the `## Governing References` section says `No governing references were resolved from the current execution snapshot.`\n\n## Observed gap\n`executeBeadResolveGoverningRefs()` builds the doc graph and looks up only by graph document ID. Path-like `spec-id` values that point to real files in the repo are dropped instead of being resolved as governing references.\n\n## Why this matters\nThis is exactly the context the execution prompt tells the agent to read before changing code or docs. When DDx drops an existing repo-relative path reference, agent execution becomes less grounded and the artifact bundle misstates the available governing context.","events_attachment":"ddx-1f434484/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-1f434484","issue_type":"bug","labels":["helix","phase:build","area:agent","area:docs","area:cli"],"priority":1,"spec-id":"FEAT-006","status":"closed","title":"Resolve path-style spec-id values in execute-bead governing references","updated_at":"2026-04-11T05:12:11.237799965Z"}
