.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:191:{"acceptance":"1. TestWorkInterrupt_InFlightAttemptUnclaimsBead verifies cancelling the work command context during an in-flight attempt releases the claim and leaves the bead open/re-claimable.\n2. TestWorkInterrupt_DoesNotSetNoProgressCooldown verifies interrupted work does not set `execute-loop-retry-after` or increment no-progress suppression.\n3. TestWorkInterrupt_RemovesClaimLiveness verifies external claim heartbeat/liveness is removed or stale-safe after cleanup.\n4. TestTryInterrupt_InFlightAttemptUnclaimsTarget verifies `ddx try \u003cid\u003e` cancellation leaves the target bead re-claimable and exits non-zero with an interrupted/signal-class outcome.\n5. TestTryInterrupt_DoesNotReportOperatorCancel verifies plain context cancellation is not classified as `operator_cancel` unless the bead cancel marker was present.\n6. TestInterruptedAfterTerminalMutation_DoesNotUndoClose verifies cancellation after a successful terminal mutation does not reopen or unclaim a closed bead.\n7. `rg -n \"context.Canceled|context_canceled|signal|operator_cancel|execute-loop-retry-after\" cli/internal/agent cli/cmd` shows cancellation paths are explicit and comments distinguish signal interruption from operator cancel.\n8. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./cmd/... ./internal/agent/... ./internal/bead/... -run \"TestWorkInterrupt|TestTryInterrupt|TestInterrupted|TestCancel|TestClaim\" -count=1` passes.\n9. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"278562820307c6dc13cbe116ebcd9bc931cd56b3","created_at":"2026-05-06T15:17:45.453929652Z","description":"PROBLEM\nAfter the root context is cancelled by Ctrl-C/SIGTERM, `ddx work` and `ddx try` must finish the TD-031 interruption path: preserve available evidence, classify the attempt as mechanically disrupted, release any non-terminal bead claim, remove runtime liveness state, and leave the unfinished bead re-claimable. The current code has partial context-cancellation classification but needs explicit end-to-end coverage for the CLI work/try paths.\n\nROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:859-878 marks non-success reports as disrupted when ctx is cancelled, but the surrounding cleanup/unclaim behavior is only incidentally covered by generic failure branches.\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:812-846 starts and stops claim heartbeat around an attempt; interrupted attempts must stop liveness and release or clear claims deterministically.\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:797-807 creates a dispatch context and only the bead-extra cancel path forces `operator_cancel`; plain context cancellation should remain `signal`/mechanical disruption, not `operator_cancel`.\n- cli/cmd/try.go:333-342 and cli/cmd/agent_cmd.go:1921-1940 propagate `cmd.Context()` into worker.Run but need regression tests that cancellation leaves the target bead re-claimable and reports the signal path.\n- docs/helix/02-design/technical-designs/TD-031-bead-state-machine.md:289-314 defines the claim release and no-cooldown requirements for worker shutdown/interruption.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n- Make interrupted attempts produce a stable disrupted/interrupted report reason (for example `context_canceled` / `signal`) without counting as model no-progress.\n- Ensure the loop unclaims interrupted non-terminal beads and removes any external claim heartbeat/liveness record.\n- Ensure interrupted attempts do not set `execute-loop-retry-after` unless a separate retryable condition was already recorded before cancellation.\n- Ensure `ddx try \u003cid\u003e` reports a clear interrupted outcome and exits non-zero after cleanup.\n- Add regression tests around worker.Run plus command-level try/work cancellation paths using controllable fake executors/runners.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Do not preserve worktrees as resumable by default. Cleanup/retry-from-scratch is the reliable default.\n- Do not alter operator cancel-marker semantics (`cancel-requested` / `operator_cancel`).\n- Do not change successful landing/review behavior when cancellation arrives after a terminal mutation.","events_attachment":"ddx-259bb4e2/events.jsonl","execute-loop-no-changes-count":1,"id":"ddx-259bb4e2","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:2","area:agent","area:beads","area:cli","kind:bug","reliability","spec:FEAT-010","spec:TD-031","interrupt"],"parent":"ddx-99a3be32","priority":0,"session_id":"eb-c5b765cd","spec-id":"FEAT-010","status":"closed","title":"agent: cleanly unwind interrupted work and try attempts","updated_at":"2026-05-06T17:26:37.476429727Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:192:{"archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","claimed-at":"2026-04-15T01:13:31Z","claimed-machine":"eitri","claimed-pid":"3766264","closing_commit_sha":"604151773f9b905346ee95b051e024a02f850cf0","created_at":"2026-04-15T01:11:17.497753676Z","description":"The embedded 'agent' harness can complete a task successfully (commit produced, tests pass) but then fail to terminate, getting stuck in a compaction retry loop with compaction always failing. The parent execute-loop never observes task_succeeded and hangs forever.\n\n## Observed\n\nRunning 'ddx agent execute-loop --once --local --harness agent --model qwen/qwen3-coder-next' against axon-43ed769b (axon auth-core-types bead):\n\n1. qwen3-coder-next ran the task correctly, producing commit 91d4bdb with 636 LOC of types + 109 green tests + clippy clean. The commit was present in the worktree at /tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-axon-43ed769b-20260415T005652-ebe7a16a.\n\n2. Instead of terminating, the agent kept generating events. After ~20 minutes the session log was 33 MB (8461+ events, 249 messages) and stuck in:\n\n    {\"type\":\"compaction.start\",...}\n    {\"type\":\"compaction.end\",...,\"data\":{\"messages_after\":249,\"messages_before\":249,\"no_compaction\":true,\"success\":false}}\n    {\"type\":\"compaction.start\",...}\n    {\"type\":\"compaction.end\",...,\"data\":{\"messages_after\":249,\"messages_before\":249,\"no_compaction\":true,\"success\":false}}\n    ...\n\n3. Parent ddx process in __futex_wait. Had to SIGTERM the parent (PID 4141811) and manually fast-forward-merge the worktree commit to land the work.\n\n4. A1 (previous bead) ran the same harness/model and terminated correctly in ~14 min with identical-looking commit shape. The difference was bead size: A2's output was a single 633-line Rust file, vs A1's 350-line SQL + 290-line test file. A2 didn't exceed what A1 did — so the context-limit explanation doesn't fully account for it.\n\n## Expected\n\n- After the agent commits and has nothing more to do, it should emit task_succeeded and terminate\n- Compaction should either succeed (messages_after \u003c messages_before) or bail out cleanly, not retry indefinitely\n- If the context genuinely cannot be compacted, the agent should report a structured failure and preserve the commits, not spin\n\n## Scope\n\n- Detect mid-turn compaction returning success=false repeatedly and bail with a structured 'compaction_stuck' status\n- Bound the total number of compaction attempts in a single turn\n- Ensure task termination happens immediately after a successful commit + no pending tool calls\n- Add a watchdog at the execute-loop level: kill the child if no commit+progress event is observed within a budget\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Session log: /Users/erik/Projects/axon/.ddx/executions/20260415T005652-ebe7a16a/embedded/agent-1776214612561376672.jsonl (33 MB)\n- Rescued commit: 91d4bdb on axon master\n- Parent process: PID 4141811 (killed)\n\n## Acceptance\n\n- [ ] Compaction retry loop is bounded and fails structurally\n- [ ] Post-commit termination path is deterministic\n- [ ] Watchdog detects and terminates stuck sessions with a preserved-commit outcome\n- [ ] Regression test reproduces the stuck state (seeded session with large no-op tool calls)","events_attachment":"ddx-25a41f51/events.jsonl","execute-loop-heartbeat-at":"2026-04-15T01:39:31.55993889Z","id":"ddx-25a41f51","issue_type":"bug","labels":["helix","area:agent","area:exec","kind:bug","gap:stability"],"owner":"ddx","priority":0,"session_id":"eb-e80e780a","status":"closed","title":"bug: embedded agent stalls in post-commit compaction loop","updated_at":"2026-04-15T03:46:00.206978601Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:194:{"acceptance":"1. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent -run TestTriageCorpus -count=1` passes.\n2. `go run ./scripts/triage/harvest-corpus.go --output library/prompts/triage/eval-corpus.jsonl` exits 0 from repo root.\n3. Running the harvester twice produces byte-identical `library/prompts/triage/eval-corpus.jsonl`.\n4. The generated eval JSONL contains at least one `expected_class=atomic` and one `expected_class=decomposable` example, or the harvester exits with a clear error explaining the missing class.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","claimed-at":"2026-04-30T14:07:51Z","claimed-machine":"sindri","claimed-pid":"4106240","closing_commit_sha":"bc1d2a42c23e4e2c5e7365f24fdf6b6f85288427","created_at":"2026-04-30T13:59:57.428273702Z","description":"Context: Parent ddx-5bf4ee7e needs a pre-claim triage gate, but the first implementable slice is the historical evidence corpus. Build a deterministic harvester that classifies historical beads into atomic/decomposable examples without invoking any agent or routing logic.\n\nIn-scope files:\n- scripts/triage/harvest-corpus.go (new)\n- library/prompts/triage/eval-corpus.jsonl (new generated eval slice)\n- cli/internal/agent/triage_test.go only for corpus loader/metric tests if needed\n\nOut-of-scope:\n- execute_bead_loop.go wiring\n- prompt invocation\n- child bead creation during work execution\n\nImplementation requirements:\n- Read .ddx/beads.jsonl from the current repo. If ../agent/.ddx/beads.jsonl exists, include it; otherwise proceed with the local repo and print a warning.\n- Classify decomposable examples from no_changes/review notes mentioning epic/split/breakdown/scope/monolithic, repeated reviewer blocks, or manually split parent/child patterns.\n- Classify atomic examples from first-attempt clean close records with small/single-subsystem scope when evidence is available.\n- Sort records deterministically and hold out 20% into library/prompts/triage/eval-corpus.jsonl using a fixed seed or stable hash.\n- Include enough fields for later prompt tests: id, title, description, acceptance, label, rationale, source_repo, expected_class, optional child_titles/child_acceptance.\n\nDo not add model/provider/harness routing policy. This is offline data preparation only.","execute-loop-heartbeat-at":"2026-04-30T14:07:51.82591567Z","id":"ddx-26058d78","issue_type":"task","labels":["area:bead-triage","area:agent","kind:feat","phase:build"],"owner":"erik","parent":"ddx-5bf4ee7e","priority":1,"status":"closed","title":"Build deterministic triage corpus harvester","updated_at":"2026-04-30T14:07:58.416409304Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:197:{"acceptance":"ddx-agent providers shows two status flags per provider: http-connected (from /v1/models) and inference-ready (from tiny probe). vidar with no model loaded shows http-connected=yes, inference-ready=no. Routing policy consumes inference-ready, not http-connected. Regression test uses a mock LM Studio that returns /v1/models but fails chat/completions.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","created_at":"2026-04-15T04:07:57.60966422Z","description":"Discovered 2026-04-15 while attempting to route tier:local tagged beads to vidar-coder. ddx-agent providers listed vidar as \"connected (8 models)\" based on GET /v1/models responding successfully, but the actual chat/completions call returned:\n\n400 Bad Request {\n  \"message\": \"No models loaded. Please load a model in the developer page or use the 'lms load' command.\",\n  \"type\": \"invalid_request_error\",\n  \"param\": \"model\",\n  \"code\": null\n}\n\nRoot cause: LM Studio /v1/models returns models available to load, not models currently in memory. An inference call to an unloaded model fails. The providers status \"connected (N models)\" is therefore a weak liveness signal — it proves the HTTP server is up but not that inference is ready.\n\nImpact on cost-tiered routing (bead ddx-dc231144 tier-based auto-escalation): the policy will mis-route work to providers that SEEM available but immediately fail on chat/completions. Every failed attempt burns time + forces escalation, defeating the cost optimization.\n\nFix: probing should attempt a tiny inference call (e.g. \"Reply with OK\") against the configured model with a short timeout. Providers that fail this probe are marked unavailable even if /v1/models responds.\n\nAlternative: parse LM Studio specific responses or add a /v1/status-like endpoint probe when the provider type is lmstudio.\n\nScope:\n- Update routing/health probe in cmd/ddx-agent/routing.go (or equivalent) to perform tiny inference probe instead of (or in addition to) models list\n- Bound probe to short timeout (e.g. 3s) and ~20 tokens max\n- Cache probe results per provider for a short TTL to avoid probing on every route decision\n- Surface the distinction in ddx agent providers output: \"connected\" vs \"inference-ready\"","id":"ddx-26e8c815","issue_type":"bug","labels":["agent","kind:bug","area:routing","area:discovery","upstream-candidate"],"notes":"Filed upstream as agent-40ee5960 in /home/erik/Projects/agent. Fix belongs in the agent repo's routing/discovery layer (not DDx CLI). This bead was a DDx-side tracking stub; closing here with upstream pointer.","priority":1,"status":"closed","title":"bug: ddx-agent providers reports 'connected' when model is unloaded — /v1/models is not a liveness probe","updated_at":"2026-04-15T04:50:52.062834781Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:198:{"acceptance":"(1) cli/internal/agent/agent_catalog_shared.go no longer reads ~/.config/agent/models.yaml.\n(2) Catalog surface translations sourced from svc.ListProfiles / ResolveProfile / ProfileAliases.\n(3) No hard-coded alias maps like \"agent.openai\" → \"embedded-openai\" remain in consumer code.\n(4) go -C cli build ./... and go -C cli test ./... green.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","created_at":"2026-04-21T01:14:26.602600556Z","description":"Land agent-1a0c0502 independent stream from parent bead ddx-7bc0c8d5. Safe to land in any order relative to the parser+GlobalProviderHealth atomic pair.\n\n## File to rewrite\n\ncli/internal/agent/agent_catalog_shared.go reads ~/.config/agent/models.yaml directly and hard-codes surface translations (\"agent.openai\" → \"embedded-openai\").\n\n## Migration target\n\n- svc.ListProfiles\n- svc.ResolveProfile\n- svc.ProfileAliases\n\nSurface translations that were hard-coded in the consumer should move to (or be obtained from) the upstream profile API.","events_attachment":"ddx-273e878a/events.jsonl","execute-loop-last-detail":"escalation exhausted: harness \"gemini\" dispatch not yet wired in service.Execute","execute-loop-last-status":"execution_failed","execute-loop-retry-after":"2026-04-21T07:55:26Z","id":"ddx-273e878a","issue_type":"task","labels":["area:agent","area:api","kind:refactor","phase:build","goal:thin-consumer","workstream:agent-upgrade"],"parent":"ddx-7bc0c8d5","priority":2,"status":"closed","title":"Remove ~/.config/agent/models.yaml parser; use svc.ListProfiles / ResolveProfile / ProfileAliases","updated_at":"2026-04-21T02:28:38.965505221Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:200:{"archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"0a7bc065e79aa1590f7f42ed0cad539158a3e130","created_at":"2026-04-29T15:20:29.65309514Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-27586b57","depends_on_id":"ddx-33e07890","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-29T15:21:00Z"}],"description":"Per plan: docs/helix/02-design/plan-2026-04-29-artifact-and-run-architecture.md.\n\nScope of PRD update:\n\n(1) Restructure Problem section into 6 clusters keyed to thesis principles in product-vision.md:\n- Abstraction (no structure / no composition / no integrity guarantees / no transferability)\n- Iteration over tracked work (no reusable work-item store / no reusable execution evidence)\n- Methodology plurality (no reusable agent dispatch — every workflow tool reinvents)\n- LLM physics (NEW cluster — token cost as a permanent constraint; nothing in current PRD)\n- Evidence/provenance (no provenance for generated artifacts; no measurement; no feedback capture)\n- Human-AI collaboration (no composition for handoffs; no discoverability; no network access)\n\nExisting problem bullets re-grouped under these headers; add the LLM-physics cluster.\n\n(2) Goals (primary): reword #1; add three-layer-architecture goal; add generated-artifact-regeneration goal; add 100% read coverage on HTTP/MCP goal.\n\n(3) Non-goals: sharpen loop wording — DDx owns mechanical queue drain (ddx work); content-aware supervisory decisions remain plugin/HELIX. Add: 'DDx does not catalog run types beyond the three layers.'\n\n(4) Feature blurbs: FEAT-001 (CLI: run/try/work top-level + ddx agent passthrough); FEAT-005 (multi-media identity); FEAT-006 (layer-1 consumer + structural passthrough); FEAT-007 (sidecar + generated_by + separate staleness); FEAT-008/021 (media-type rendering + regenerate + layer-aware run views); FEAT-010 (3-layer architecture + substrate unification); FEAT-019 (child of FEAT-010 — evaluation UX, workflow shapes -\u003e skills).\n\nSummary: artifacts (multi-media); three-layer run architecture; one substrate; invocation upstream.\n\nDo NOT touch docs/helix/01-frame/principles.md.","events_attachment":"ddx-27586b57/events.jsonl","execute-loop-no-changes-count":1,"id":"ddx-27586b57","issue_type":"task","labels":["frame","plan-2026-04-29"],"notes":"REVIEW:BLOCK\n\nDiff under review contains only execution evidence files (manifest.json, result.json) and no changes to docs/helix/01-frame/prd.md. The PRD restructure required by the bead is not present in this diff and cannot be evaluated.","priority":1,"session_id":"eb-86ea1eff","status":"closed","title":"[artifact-run-arch] update prd.md for artifact + 3-layer architecture","updated_at":"2026-04-30T00:33:33.799167898Z"}
