.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:253:{"acceptance":"(1) `ddx agent execute-bead \u003cid\u003e --provider vidar` routes to vidar unambiguously. (2) `ddx agent execute-loop --model-ref code-medium` resolves via the model catalog. (3) `ddx agent execute-loop --model qwen/qwen3-coder-next` with NO provider/ref flag errors out with the message described above (regression test required). (4) `ddx agent execute-loop --model qwen/qwen3-coder-next --provider vidar-coder` works correctly and routes to vidar. (5) Unit or integration test covers the orphan-model error case. (6) `go build ./...` passes. (7) `go test ./cli/cmd/... ./cli/internal/agent/... -count=1` passes.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"f8b5012c12d382bc270d0b9b2693d48c4bab05f8","created_at":"2026-04-14T20:34:10.670010663Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-35af61e8","depends_on_id":"ddx-3d64fd16","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-14T20:34:11Z"}],"description":"The real bug fix from the vidar→OpenRouter silent-fallback incident. Update cli/cmd/agent_cmd.go (execute-loop) and cli/cmd/agent_execute_bead.go (execute-bead) to accept three NEW flags alongside the existing --harness and --model:\n\n- --provider \u003cname\u003e: passes through to ddx-agent as its `-provider` flag. Selects a named provider from   config (e.g. `vidar`, `vidar-coder`, `openrouter`).\n- --model-ref \u003cref\u003e: passes through as `-model-ref`. Resolves via the model catalog to a canonical target   (e.g. `code-high`, `code-medium`).\n- --model \u003cstring\u003e: already exists. Currently passed to ddx-agent as `-model` which does a direct model   override. THE FIX: when --model is given but no matching provider can serve it AND no catalog alias   matches AND no --provider/--model-ref is set, DDx must error BEFORE dispatching the agent — \"model 'X'   did not match any provider, catalog ref, or model-route; specify --provider or --model-ref explicitly\".   Do NOT silently fall back to the default provider (which was how --model qwen/qwen3-coder-next routed to   OpenRouter earlier).\n\nWire the new flags through RunOptions / ExecuteBeadOptions / ExecuteBeadLoopOptions so they reach the Runner.RunAgent in internal/agent/agent_runner.go, which then forwards them to agentlib provider resolution.","events_attachment":"ddx-35af61e8/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-35af61e8","issue_type":"task","labels":["ddx","phase:build","kind:agent-routing","area:agent","area:cli"],"parent":"ddx-bd0691fe","priority":1,"status":"closed","title":"Visibility 7: teach execute-loop + execute-bead about --provider and --model-ref, error on orphan --model","updated_at":"2026-04-15T04:48:44.097242174Z"}
