lProviderHealth singleton + ProviderHealthTracker.\n\n## Call sites to migrate\n\n- workers.go:511 (IsHealthy) / :593 (Mark)\n- agent_cmd.go:1702 (IsHealthy) / :1791 (Mark)\n- agent_cmd.go:680 (routing_signal.CurrentQuota.State == \"blocked\")\n- agent_cmd.go:704 (ReadClaudeQuotaRoutingDecision)\n\n## Migration target\n\n- svc.ListHarnesses — HarnessInfo.Quota / UsageWindows / Account\n- svc.ListProviders — ProviderInfo.EndpointStatus\n- svc.RouteStatus — RouteStatusReport with RouteCandidateStatus.Healthy\n- svc.RecordRouteAttempt — RouteAttempt with status/reason\n\nVocabulary translation shim in buildProviderSummary / buildProviderDetail maps current \"fresh/stale\" to upstream's \"ok/stale/unavailable\" (consumer-side mapping only; not an upstream API change).\n\n## Observable behavior changes (consumer surfaces)\n\n- ddx agent doctor --routing --json: state.claude_quota_decision field disappears.\n- ddx agent doctor --routing human text: claude-quota-cache line disappears.\n- ProbeHarnessState via state.go.\n- ddx agent usage enrichment.\n- REST /api/providers.\n- MCP ddx_provider_list / ddx_provider_show.\n\nNot affected: SvelteKit frontend providers page uses GraphQL providerStatuses only (no cache fields).","events_attachment":"ddx-3610f1fc/events.jsonl","execute-loop-heartbeat-at":"2026-04-21T01:50:25.583208217Z","id":"ddx-3610f1fc","issue_type":"task","labels":["area:agent","area:routing","kind:refactor","phase:build","goal:thin-consumer","workstream:agent-upgrade"],"owner":"ddx","parent":"ddx-7bc0c8d5","priority":2,"session_id":"eb-414c8ef8","status":"closed","title":"Remove provider-native parsers and GlobalProviderHealth shadow (atomic)","updated_at":"2026-04-21T01:55:43.260389079Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:260:{"acceptance":"- [ ] Decision recorded as a notes update on ddx-1bf6c0df (file-delete bead) explicitly stating: keep tier_escalation.go in DDx; bead re-scoped to \"ensure file does not depend on routing.go internals\"\n- [ ] Decision also recorded as notes on ddx-334d41cb (cmd tier-escalation migration) and ddx-3bf91ebf (server tier-escalation migration) so their migration approach is unambiguous (DDx-internal symbols stay; just decouple from routing.go)\n- [ ] tier_escalation.go inventory: every external dependency (agent.X) classified as keep-in-DDx OR replace-with-service","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","claimed-at":"2026-04-19T03:10:33Z","claimed-machine":"eitri","claimed-pid":"302710","created_at":"2026-04-19T02:38:22.348739884Z","description":"Decide where tier-escalation logic lives (TiersInRange, TierAttemptRecord, FormatTierAttemptBody, AppendEscalationSummaryEvent, ShouldEscalate, ModelTier, AdaptiveMinTier) and update bead scopes accordingly.\n\nTwo options:\nA. Keep in DDx — these are bead-driven orchestration concerns (per-attempt evidence appending, adaptive min-tier promotion based on cheap-tier success rate). They wrap the per-call service.Execute with retry-on-tier-mismatch. Not LLM routing per se; bead routing.\nB. Move to agent — package as a stall-style policy on ExecuteRequest (StallPolicy already enforces some retry; could extend to TierPolicy).\n\nRecommendation: A. Tier escalation is bead-driven workflow logic (consults DDx-side adaptive min-tier from execution evidence), not per-LLM-call concern. Should stay in DDx as a thin orchestration wrapper around service.Execute.\n\nOutcome of this bead: tier_escalation.go stays in DDx; the file-delete bead ddx-1bf6c0df is RE-SCOPED to \"ensure tier_escalation.go does not depend on routing.go internals\" rather than \"delete the file.\" Update bead notes accordingly.","execute-loop-heartbeat-at":"2026-04-19T03:10:33.016266096Z","id":"ddx-378d381f","issue_type":"decision","labels":["phase:design","area:agent","kind:scope"],"notes":"DECISION: Tier-escalation stays in DDx as orchestration logic.\n\nVERIFIED: cli/internal/agent/tier_escalation.go currently imports only stdlib + internal/bead. Zero external dependencies on routing.go, state.go, registry.go, or any to-be-deleted file.\n\nSymbols defined in tier_escalation.go (used by cmd/agent_cmd.go and server/workers.go): AdaptiveMinTier, AdaptiveMinTierResult, ProviderHealthTracker, TiersInRange, ShouldEscalate, FormatTierAttemptBody, TierAttemptRecord, EscalationSummary, BuildEscalationSummary, AppendEscalationSummaryEvent, classifyAttemptTier (private). ModelTier itself lives in models.go (also stays).\n\nCONSEQUENCES:\n- ddx-1bf6c0df (was \"delete tier_escalation.go\") is now NO-OP: file stays as-is. Re-scope to confirmation: \"tier_escalation.go has no dependency on routing.go internals\" (already true).\n- ddx-334d41cb (cmd tier-escalation migration) is now NO-OP: cmd already calls agent.TiersInRange etc. and those stay.\n- ddx-3bf91ebf (server tier-escalation migration) is now NO-OP for the tier symbols themselves; only the deprecated AgentRunnerFactory field deletion remains scoped.","owner":"erik","parent":"ddx-62b04ccd","priority":1,"status":"closed","title":"Decision: tier-escalation logic stays in DDx (re-scope clarification)","updated_at":"2026-04-19T03:11:16.147837393Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:262:{"acceptance":"1. **Root cause #1 fixed:** `attempted[candidate.ID] = struct{}{}` is moved to AFTER the pre-claim hook succeeds. Regression test in `execute_bead_loop_test.go` asserts: with a fake `PreClaimHook` that fails on the first call and succeeds thereafter, the loop processes the same bead on the second iteration (not skipped because of stale `attempted` state).\n\n2. **Root cause #2 fixed:** the post-`Execute` outcome-handling block (lines ~510-862) does not exit the loop on transient `Store.*` errors. Each `return result, err` in that block is converted to: log the error, emit a `kind:loop-error` bead event when possible, set the bead to a short cooldown, and `continue` to the next iteration. The only exception is context cancellation (`ctx.Err()`), which still terminates immediately.\n\n3. **Regression tests for AC-2:** for each `Store.*` call in the outcome block (Unclaim, IncrNoChangesCount, adjudicateNoChanges, CloseWithEvidence on each path, Reopen on each path, SetExecutionCooldown on each path, late AppendEvent), a test injects a transient error from a fake store and asserts: (a) the loop continues, (b) a `kind:loop-error` event is recorded with the failing operation name, (c) `result.Failures++` advances.\n\n4. **End-to-end reproduction guard:** an integration test seeds a bead.jsonl with 3 ready beads. The first returns `no_changes` (executor fake), the second returns `success`, the third returns `already_satisfied`. The loop runs to completion (all three processed) without exiting prematurely. With the pre-fix loop, this test fails on the first bead.\n\n5. **Worker-state semantics preserved:** existing tests that assert worker.State transitions (`running` → `exited` / `failed` / `stopped` / `reaped`) still pass. The fix changes loop *advancement*, not terminal-state classification.\n\n6. **Documented behavior:** `docs/agents/execute-loop.md` (or the closest existing doc) gains a \"loop termination\" section listing the only conditions that terminate the loop: context cancellation, `Once == true`, `PollInterval \u003c= 0` AND `nextCandidate` returns no candidate, `RoutePreflight` rejected. Explicitly states that Store errors during outcome handling do NOT terminate the loop.\n\n7. **Operator workaround retired:** the README's \"if `ddx work` exits early, restart it\" guidance (or equivalent) is removed; that workaround was masking this bug.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"1495ba706ffdc0e7bfb4833487ed068ffe732aeb","created_at":"2026-04-29T19:05:38.552407002Z","description":"## Symptom\n\n`ddx work` (no `--once` flag, no `--poll-interval`, default mode) exits after processing exactly one bead instead of draining the queue. Reproduced four times today on `/home/erik/Projects/agent` with `--harness lmstudio` pinned (which sidesteps the unrelated `ddx-c7081f89` server-worker tier-walk issue):\n\n| Run | Outcome on first bead | Worker terminal state | Queue still non-empty? |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 2 | `already_satisfied` (`agent-4aa3584e` adjudicated satisfied) | `already_satisfied` / `exited` | yes — 2 ready beads remained |\n| 3 | pre-claim hook rejected (diverged branch) | `exited`, attempts=0 | yes |\n| 4 | pre-claim hook rejected (diverged branch) | `exited`, attempts=0 | yes |\n| 5 | `no_changes` from agent (`agent-6c7a4c11` declined as epic; bead left **claimed**) | `exited`, attempts=1 | yes — 5 ready beads remained |\n\nIn all four runs the loop should have continued to the next ready bead. Per `agent/.claude/skills/ddx/reference/work.md`, only `success`/`already_satisfied` close the bead and `no_changes`/`land_conflict`/`*_failed` unclaim and continue. None of these outcomes is documented or expected to be loop-terminal.\n\n## Root cause #1 (verified)\n\n`cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:382`:\n\n```go\nattempted[candidate.ID] = struct{}{}\n\n// Pre-claim hook: fetch origin + verify ancestry before claiming.\n// On error the bead is skipped for this iteration; the loop\n// continues (ctx is not cancelled).\nif runtime.PreClaimHook != nil {\n    if hookErr := runtime.PreClaimHook(ctx); hookErr != nil {\n        // ... log + emit ...\n        continue\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThe bead is added to `attempted` **before** the pre-claim hook runs. On hook failure (e.g. diverged branch), the loop `continue`s but the bead stays in `attempted`. Next iteration, `nextCandidate()` (line 924) skips the still-ready bead because it's in `attempted`, returns `ok=false`, and the loop exits at line 374 because `PollInterval \u003c= 0`. Single-shot exit with `attempts=0`.\n\n**Reproduces:** runs 3 and 4 above.\n\n## Root cause #2 (suspected — needs targeted instrumentation)\n\nRuns 2 and 5 reached `Execute()` and got a real report back. Worker log shows the entry line `▶ \u003cbead\u003e: \u003ctitle\u003e` but no closing `✓ \u003cbead\u003e → \u003cresult\u003e` line (which is written at line 909). That means the loop exited somewhere between line 488 (`Executor.Execute`) and line 909 (the final summary log).\n\nBetween those bounds, **at least 16 distinct `return result, err` points** trigger if any `Store.*` operation returns an error: `Unclaim` (711, 700), `IncrNoChangesCount` (717), `adjudicateNoChanges` (721), `CloseWithEvidence` (520, 615, 694, 739), `Reopen` (635, 669), `SetExecutionCooldown` (749, 791, 803, 835, 844), late `AppendEvent` (862). Any single transient store error during outcome handling kills the worker.\n\nFor run 5 specifically, `agent-6c7a4c11` is now `Status: in_progress` with `Owner: ddx, Machine: sindri`. The bead was **never unclaimed** despite the agent returning `no_changes` — meaning the loop exited on or before line 711 (`w.Store.Unclaim`) failing. Investigation should look at what error `Unclaim` would return when called against a bead the same worker claimed seconds earlier; possible candidates: tracker-write race with concurrent worker, bead.jsonl re-write during a fetch by the pre-claim hook on a later iteration that already happened (no — pre-claim is pre-claim, not post-execute), or a malformed bead row that fails store-side validation.\n\nIndependent of the specific store error: the structural pattern of \"any Store.* error → exit the entire loop\" is the wrong default. A store error on outcome handling should at most park the bead and continue to the next, never terminate the worker.\n\n## Why this is loadbearing\n\nThe loop is the queue-drain primitive. Every observed failure-to-drain in the last 24 hours of operator complaints traces back to this — beads that should have been the worker's second/third/fourth attempt never got picked up because the worker exited after one attempt, and the operator manually restarts the drain (sometimes after a long delay). The visible queue depth is misleading: half the \"ready\" beads are sitting behind a worker that quietly died.\n\n## In-scope files\n\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go` — fixes for both root causes\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop_test.go` — regression tests for each path\n\n## Out of scope\n\n- Anything in the `agent` SDK (`/home/erik/Projects/agent`). The loop and all its store interactions are owned by ddx.\n- The pre-claim hook's divergence-detection logic itself — that's correct behavior; the bug is how the loop reacts to the hook's signal.\n- Adaptive min-tier / tier-walk machinery (`ddx-c7081f89`, `ddx-aec9d68c`) — independent.\n\n## Anti-goals\n\n- Do **not** swallow store errors silently. They must be surfaced (event + log) but should not kill the worker on transient/per-bead failures.\n- Do **not** convert the loop's Once/PollInterval semantics — they're correct.\n- Do **not** change worker terminal-state semantics (`exited`/`failed`/`stopped`/`reaped`).","events_attachment":"ddx-37cdb43a/events.jsonl","execute-loop-no-changes-count":1,"id":"ddx-37cdb43a","issue_type":"bug","labels":["area:execute-loop","kind:bug","phase:fix"],"notes":"REVIEW:BLOCK\n\nDiff only contains execution evidence (manifest.json + result.json) under .ddx/executions/. No changes to execute_bead_loop.go, tests, or docs are visible, so none of the 7 acceptance criteria can be evaluated as implemented.","priority":0,"session_id":"eb-842ed336","status":"closed","title":"execute-loop: ddx work exits after one bead instead of draining the queue","updated_at":"2026-04-30T00:04:15.728726551Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:267:{"acceptance":"1. Sanitized fixture corpus includes Claude, Codex/Fizeau, native, long-output, long-path, turn-counter, and tok/sec samples.\n2. Tests assert rendered output preserves important basenames, shows turn_index counting up, includes output bytes/lines/excerpt where present, and includes tok/sec only when calculable.\n3. Tests avoid arbitrary \u003c40 character limits; normal lines target 72-80 characters with the SD-011 documented 120-character tool-command exception.\n4. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent -run \"Test.*Progress|TestFormatSessionLogLines|Test.*Corpus\" -count=1 passes.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"655d594893c857c48e97fbe73da5d093f4318d80","created_at":"2026-05-05T13:40:40.976887273Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-38f694b2","depends_on_id":"ddx-83e3687b","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-05T13:40:49Z"}],"description":"Build a DDx golden corpus for rendering canonical progress and legacy fallback samples. The corpus should include representative Claude, Codex, native/Fizeau, and at least one secondary harness sample. It exists to prevent regressions like over-truncated paths, invisible turn counters, missing output summaries, and missing LLM throughput.\n\nIn-scope files:\n- cli/internal/agent test fixtures and formatter/progress tests\n- historical sample extraction into small sanitized fixtures\n\nRequired samples:\n- Claude stream-style historical records\n- Codex/Fizeau progress-style records\n- Native agent records\n- \u003cout ... lines\u003e or equivalent long-output summaries\n- long paths including cli/internal/agent/session_log_format.go\n- turn_index values 21, 22, and 23\n- LLM response timing and token usage sufficient to render tok/sec\n\nOut-of-scope:\n- Storing millions of raw logs in the repository.\n- Live provider execution.","events_attachment":"ddx-38f694b2/events.jsonl","execute-loop-no-changes-count":1,"id":"ddx-38f694b2","issue_type":"task","labels":["area:agent","area:test","area:progress","kind:quality","upstream-fizeau"],"parent":"ddx-dda48755","priority":0,"session_id":"eb-c54bb47e","spec-id":"SD-011","status":"closed","title":"Add progress rendering corpus for canonical and legacy samples","updated_at":"2026-05-06T09:48:00.86557622Z"}
.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:270:{"acceptance":"1. The `git show`/`git diff` call that produces the \u003cdiff\u003e section of a \u003cbead-review\u003e prompt passes a pathspec that excludes `.ddx/executions/*/embedded/*`, `.ddx/executions/*/prompt.md`, `.ddx/executions/*/usage.json`, and `.ddx/executions/*/manifest.json`. Verified by reading the updated implementations in `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_review.go:gitShow` and `cli/cmd/bead_review.go:beadReviewGitShow` — both invoke `git show \u003crev\u003e -- . ':(exclude)...'` (or functional equivalent) with the documented exclusion set.\n\n2. Regression test: a unit test builds a \u003cbead-review\u003e prompt against a synthetic evidence commit whose diff adds a `.ddx/executions/\u003cattempt\u003e/embedded/agent-fake.jsonl` containing \u003e=20,000 `+`-prefixed lines. The test asserts the resulting prompt is below a fixed token budget (suggest 150k tokens, ~600k bytes) and does NOT contain any line matching `agent-fake.jsonl`.\n\n3. Token-budget guard: a unit test asserts that when a `\u003cbead-review\u003e` prompt would exceed 150k tokens even after the exclusion, the builder elides to a summary stub (per suggested fix #2) and logs a warning rather than emitting the full content.\n\n4. Execution-evidence staging exclusion: `landEvidence` (`cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_land.go`) and `VerifyCleanWorktree` (`cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:VerifyCleanWorktree`) stage the evidence directory with a pathspec that excludes `embedded/` (matching the existing `SynthesizeCommit` exclusion at `execute_bead.go:269-283`), OR move raw session logs out of the tracked evidence directory entirely (suggested fix #3). Covered by a regression test that runs a complete execute-bead attempt end-to-end in a temporary repo and asserts `git log -p --follow '.ddx/executions/*/embedded/*.jsonl'` returns nothing (no tracked session log).\n\n5. End-to-end reproduction of the `hx-dd4ab35f`-style scenario: an integration test simulates the nexiq sequence (attempt lands impl commit, evidence commit adds 20k-line session log, review-malfunction triggers retry) and asserts the retry's synthesized `prompt.md` is under the budget cap AND the review call succeeds against a stub provider without an n_keep/n_ctx error.\n\n6. Existing execution evidence continues to satisfy auditability: either still tracked but excluded from review diffs, or moved to a dedicated ref / ignored store per the chosen fix. `ddx agent metrics` and `ddx bead metrics` still surface per-attempt usage/tokens/cost from the evidence bundle after the fix.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","claimed-at":"2026-04-18T00:13:24Z","claimed-machine":"eitri","claimed-pid":"1551897","created_at":"2026-04-17T22:08:23.667089738Z","description":"## Summary\n\nOn retry, DDx synthesizes a \u003cbead-review\u003e prompt whose \u003cdiff\u003e section is the output of `git show \u003cresultRev\u003e`. When the prior attempt's landing sequence appended an evidence commit of the form `chore: add execution evidence [\u003cattempt_id\u003e]` that added `.ddx/executions/\u003cattempt_id\u003e/embedded/agent-*.jsonl` (full per-event NDJSON session log) as a tracked file, `resultRev` is that evidence commit's SHA (because `landEvidence` sets `result.NewTip = sha` and the orchestrator copies `land.NewTip` into `res.ResultRev`). `git show` of the evidence commit emits the entire session log diff with a `+` prefix per line. Session logs are 5-50k lines; the retry prompt exceeds every public context window.\n\n## Category / severity / surface\n\n- Category: correctness / resource-exhaustion\n- Severity: high\n- Surface: `ddx agent execute-bead` retry path triggered by `kind:review-malfunction` (and any other flow that re-synthesizes a \u003cbead-review\u003e prompt from a git diff/show since base_rev).\n\n## Full bug description (verbatim)\n\nOn retry, DDx synthesizes a \u003cbead-review\u003e prompt whose \u003cdiff\u003e section is the raw `git diff \u003cbase_rev\u003e..\u003cresult_rev\u003e` of the prior attempt. The prior attempt's landing sequence includes an evidence commit of the form:\n\n    chore: add execution evidence [\u003cattempt_id\u003e]\n\nthat adds `.ddx/executions/\u003cattempt_id\u003e/embedded/agent-*.jsonl` — the full per-event NDJSON session log of the prior attempt — as a tracked file. Because that file is *added* in the diff range, the diff includes it in full with a `+` prefix on every line. Session logs are routinely 5-50k lines. One reasonable fix iteration is enough to push the retry prompt past 1-2 million tokens, which no currently supported model can accept — the provider streams back an n_keep \u003e n_ctx error and the retry crashes without a request round-trip.\n\nThis is a self-poisoning loop: the \"evidence\" DDx commits to make attempts auditable is the exact artifact that makes the next attempt undeliverable.\n\n## Reproduction (observed live 2026-04-17 in nexiq)\n\n1. Bead `hx-dd4ab35f` claimed by execute-loop worker (harness=agent, model=qwen/qwen3.6-35b-a3b, provider=vidar).\n2. Attempt `20260417T211600-d6a7dee6` succeeded and landed two commits: `cb5e733` (implementation + regression test [hx-dd4ab35f]) and `9a006dd` (chore: add execution evidence [20260417T211600-], adds `.ddx/executions/20260417T211600-d6a7dee6/embedded/agent-1776460560227794836.jsonl`, +20,623 lines).\n3. Post-merge review emitted `BLOCK` without a rationale; DDx recorded `kind:review-malfunction` and reopened the bead for retry.\n4. Retry `20260417T212928-27f9054a` synthesized `.ddx/executions/20260417T212928-27f9054a/prompt.md` of 6,307,997 bytes; `\u003cbead-review\u003e` block = 6,307,969 bytes; 99.9998% is the diff of the prior evidence commit, 99%+ of that diff is the session log file. Rest of \u003cbead-review\u003e (title/description/acceptance/labels/governing) is ~28 bytes.\n5. lmstudio responded: \"n_keep: 2,274,074 \u003e= n_ctx: 196,608\". Worker recorded failed attempt with zero usage. Same pattern on vidar (n_keep: 1,169,147) and bragi (n_keep: 2,274,074), all running qwen3.6-35b-a3b at max_context_length 262144. Provider/model is irrelevant — prompt exceeds every public context window.\n\n## DDx code-path verification (Claude investigation 2026-04-17)\n\nRelevant files and line ranges in /Users/erik/Projects/ddx:\n\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_review.go:553-561` — `DefaultBeadReviewer.gitShow(rev)` runs `git -C \u003cprojectRoot\u003e show \u003crev\u003e` with no pathspec. Output is injected raw into `\u003cdiff\u003e` by `BuildReviewPrompt` at `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_review.go:383-384`.\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_review.go:427-431` — reviewer fetches `diff := r.gitShow(resultRev)` then builds the prompt.\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_land.go:540-555` (`landEvidence`) — creates `chore: add execution evidence [\u003cshort\u003e]` and sets `result.NewTip = sha`.\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_land.go:428-434` — `RealLandingGitOps.StageDir` runs `git add -- \u003crelPath\u003e` on the entire `.ddx/executions/\u003cattempt\u003e/` directory with no exclusions for `embedded/`.\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_orchestrator.go:250-251` — after Land, `res.ResultRev = land.NewTip`, so `ResultRev` ends up pointing at the evidence commit. The reviewer then runs `git show \u003cevidence-commit\u003e`, which is literally the dump of the session log.\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:1135-1164` (`VerifyCleanWorktree`) — also stages the evidence dir via `git add -- \u003cevidenceDir\u003e` and commits `chore: add execution evidence [\u003cshort\u003e]`; same no-exclusion pattern.\n- `cli/cmd/bead_review.go:162-171` (`beadReviewGitShow`) — mirror of the same bug in the standalone `ddx bead review` command.\n\nConfirmation the bug reporter's claim about `:(exclude).ddx/executions/*/embedded`:\n- `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:269-283` (`SynthesizeCommit`) — the exclusion pathspec IS present here; the bug is that the evidence-landing commit path (`StageDir` + `VerifyCleanWorktree`) and the review path (`git show \u003crev\u003e`) do not share this exclusion.\n- `cli/cmd/init.go:19-46` — the gitignore rules DO include `.ddx/executions/*/embedded/`, but `git add -- \u003cdir\u003e` on pre-existing or explicitly-added paths can still stage, and older workspaces may pre-date this gitignore (matches nexiq's scenario where the evidence commit landed the session log).\n\n## Deviation from bug description (minor)\n\nThe bug text describes the diff as `git diff \u003cbase_rev\u003e..\u003cresult_rev\u003e`. The code actually does `git show \u003cresultRev\u003e` (single-rev show). The self-poisoning mechanism is functionally identical: when `resultRev` points at the evidence commit (`landEvidence` + `res.ResultRev = land.NewTip`), `git show` emits the entire `+`-prefixed session log. All suggested fixes still apply.\n\n## Suggested fixes (ascending scope)\n\n1. Exclude execution-evidence paths from bead-review diffs by passing a pathspec to the `git show`/`git diff` call in the prompt builder: `-- . ':(exclude).ddx/executions/*/embedded/*' ':(exclude).ddx/executions/*/prompt.md' ':(exclude).ddx/executions/*/usage.json'`. The same exclusion already exists at `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:269-283` for `SynthesizeCommit`; replicate it in `DefaultBeadReviewer.gitShow` (`execute_bead_review.go:553-561`), `beadReviewGitShow` (`cli/cmd/bead_review.go:162-171`), `landEvidence` → `StageDir` (`execute_bead_land.go:428-434,540-555`), and `VerifyCleanWorktree` (`execute_bead.go:1135-1164`).\n2. Substitute, don't reproduce. When a tracked-file addition exceeds a byte/line budget in the diff, replace it with a one-line stub such as: `+++ b/.ddx/executions/.../agent-*.jsonl  (+20,623 lines of session evidence — omitted from review prompt)`.\n3. Stop committing raw session logs as tracked evidence. Move `.ddx/executions/*/embedded/*.jsonl` to a gitignored store, or a separate `refs/ddx/evidence/*` ref analogous to `refs/ddx/iterations/*`.\n4. Cap the \u003cbead-review\u003e prompt size with a hard budget (e.g., 150k tokens). Elide to summary + log warning when exceeded.\n\n(1) is the minimal surgical fix; (3) is the correct long-term fix.\n\n## Evidence in nexiq repo\n\n- Bloated retry prompt: `.ddx/executions/20260417T212928-27f9054a/prompt.md` (6,307,997 bytes; \u003cbead-review\u003e body = 6,307,969 bytes).\n- Successful prior attempt: `.ddx/executions/20260417T211600-d6a7dee6/` (landed cb5e733 + 9a006dd).\n- Failing agent session: `.ddx/agent-logs/agent-1776460487823541600.jsonl` (session.end payload has the n_keep/n_ctx error verbatim).\n- Bead event trail: `ddx bead show hx-dd4ab35f` — routing, then `kind:review-malfunction summary:BLOCK without rationale`, then `kind:execute-bead summary:review_malfunction`.","execute-loop-heartbeat-at":"2026-04-18T00:13:24.428420423Z","id":"ddx-39e27896","issue_type":"bug","labels":["ddx","phase:build","kind:bug","area:agent","area:execute-bead","area:prompt-synthesis"],"owner":"erik","priority":0,"spec-id":"FEAT-006","status":"closed","title":"execute-bead retry prompt explodes when prior attempt committed session-log evidence","updated_at":"2026-04-18T00:29:15.347462806Z"}
