.ddx/beads-archive.jsonl:341:{"acceptance":"(1) ddx agent metrics tier-success queries execution evidence and reports success rate per harness/model tier (local, sonnet, opus, etc.) based on result.json outcome field. Output includes: tier, attempts, successes, success_rate, avg_cost_usd, avg_duration_ms. (2) Supports --last N flag to limit to most recent N attempts (default: all). (3) cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./cmd -run TestAgentMetricsTierSuccess -count=1 passes. (4) cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./cmd -count=1 passes (no regressions).","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","created_at":"2026-04-16T20:28:19.822065577Z","description":"## Scope\nAdd ddx agent metrics tier-success command that aggregates execution outcomes by harness/model tier.\n\n## Context\nExecution evidence result.json records harness, concrete model (via manifest.json or result.json), outcome (task_succeeded/task_failed/etc.), cost_usd, and duration_ms. This command aggregates those into tier-level success rates to inform routing policy.\n\n## Files to touch\n- cli/cmd/agent_metrics.go — new subcommand under ddx agent metrics\n- cli/cmd/agent.go — register metrics subcommand group\n- cli/cmd/agent_metrics_test.go — test with fixture execution dirs\n\n## Implementation notes\n- Scan .ddx/executions/*/result.json for harness and outcome fields\n- Group by harness (or harness+model if useful) \n- Calculate success rate = count(task_succeeded) / count(all)\n- Include avg cost and duration per tier","events_attachment":"ddx-4cdb9600/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-4cdb9600","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:build","area:agent","area:cli","kind:measurement"],"parent":"ddx-4b59b816","priority":1,"status":"closed","title":"Tier success-rate analytics: ddx agent metrics tier-success","updated_at":"2026-04-16T21:49:28.836550287Z"}
